text:
i don't want to be a victim
i always feel like i'm just being dramatic
but some days i can barely stand my parents touching me
i shrink away when my dad tries to hug me
i jump when my mom pats my shoulder
some nights i lay in bed my mind a movie screen and i
the lead of the scene
which plays over and over in my mind
as i try to figure out where i went wrong
i'm sick to my stomach, screaming in my head
but no tears run down my face
because even after all these years
even after time after time i'm told it wasn't my fault
their still are people who say it was
and the voice in my head says that i had to have done something
i can't live in a world where people rape innocent five year olds
if i did something wrong then at least she wasn't just completely a predator
then every stranger i meet isn't a rapist
i don't want to be a victim forever
so many people have been sexually assaulted fuck
1 in 6 women are raped in their lives
every 98 seconds an american is assaulted
and i'm still broken over something that happened 10 years ago
i don't want to be a victim,
i don't even want to be a survivor
all i want is to be clean

#poetry #mentalillness #rapesurvivor #rapepoem #depressionpoetry #metoo

text:
the future is female: an experiment - 
this was my first time wearing this dress and let me tell you, it was an insane learning experience. i learned so much about how other people view feminism today. i got a lot of turned heads but i also got a lot of hell yeah! that’s dope! 
by saying “the future is female” it does not mean we are saying the future isn’t everyone else’s. by saying the future is female, we’re saying the future is where we strive to make all smaller voices heard because we have been silenced for way too long. with that being said, we all have our story. personally, i am a victim, not a “statistic”. i am a woman, not 1 in 3. i am a person that did not deserve what happened to me. so are all of you. make your voices heard. educate those around you. make a difference. as a female, the future is yours so don’t let anyone especially your abusers take that from you. i love you guys. thank you for listening. and if you ever need a friend, i’m here. please reach out. i know first hand, it’s one of the toughest experiences a person ever has to deal with. 
thank you, @thinking_boutique for helping me make this bold statement with this beautiful piece. they have no idea the strength of the woman wearing it. the future is female and it starts with us. 💙❤️ #metoo #thefutureisfemale #styledbytb #thefutureisnow #survivor #thinkingboutique #houstonstyle #houstoninfluencer #empowerment #survivor #girlpower #style #believewomen #hero @undiscoveredbum 📸

text:
fast and furious director rob cohen has been accused by his daughter of raping her as a child. his daughter was born a boy, but now goes by the name valkyrie weather and identifies as female. however the attack occurred during childhood, long before her transition. she revealed the news on facebook yesterday saying, “when i was very young, rob (cohen) used my body for his own sexual gratification. my mother witnessed one of the assaults when i was between two and two and a half years old, and has since confirmed what she saw. this fact has cost me more than i could ever convey here. rob has also raped at least one other woman, in her sleep. i know this because he would occasionally tell the story as an anecdote. presumably in an effort to turn me into the straight son that he wanted me to be, rob took me to see sex workers and establishments in thailand and the czech republic starting when i was as young as 13/14 years old. through therapy and support from loved ones, i no longer feel that i owe this man any loyalty. and thanks to the #metoo movement, i have found the will to speak out. while rob will in all likelihood escape criminal justice, i demand that my story be heard. i am not seeking financial restitution, nor do i have a career to promote. my greatest hope is that others who have been hurt by rob cohen feel that they are able to come forward as well.” rob has denied the allegations and released a statement saying, “knowing that it is categorically untrue is painful enough. having to write this and saying that my kid is not telling the truth is heart wrenching. when valkyrie’s mom and i were getting divorced, she accused me during the custody court proceedings of many things, including a similar accusation to this one. after a very long trial, the court appointed psychiatrist awarded me full custody, in spite of these false accusations. subsequently, my ex-wife appealed, and after another lengthy trial, i was awarded full custody once again. at this point kyle was about 14 years old, and when asked about his preference on which parent to live with, he chose me. never ever would i harm any of my children, or any child for that matter.”
source: nme

text:
it’s been a rough—stop right there.
today i thought about how i’ve been telling everyone in my life, “the past few weeks have been challenging.” and sure, they have. something in the realm of sexual assault to me happened two weeks ago.
.
.
i sort of knew this person. i wasn’t sure what was happening—and it took me a few days to even call it sexual assault.
.
.
it’s stirred up a lot of emotions. i drank. i smoked weed. i avoided things. i didn’t sleep super well. i shut down.
.
.
and then i had some very powerful conversations with the people involved. i got clear on my boundaries, how i felt violated, and what i hoped for in the future.
.
.
thing is, everyone has something rough going on in their lives. sexual assault is one of the myriad things people live through and cope with. i’m not diminishing this experience, it was shitty. and i reverted back to my old ways of coping. guess what? same results.
.
.
i’ll share more on this in the future, but for now, i hope you’ll appreciate that i did finally come to my senses (much quicker than ever before thanks to good friends) about my coping mechanisms and am continuing on the #soberparty journey and practicing more yoga/self care/etc bc that part of my life was definitely missing in my recent move.
.
.
yes, i was sober when this happened. and no it didn’t not change the fact that this happened. sobriety is not the answer to all your problems. for me, it’s simply a lens through which i choose to view myself and my world that gives me so much power and freedom.
.
.
i choose how i respond, grow, and process. life doesn’t happen to me, i create it every. single. day. you can too. .
thanks for listening. love you all to the moon + back. 
xx, court #soberparty #metoo

judge dennis porter signed the order. no-bail arrest warrants does not necessarily mean that kelly won't eventually be offered bail once appearing in court to answer the charges.

the charges filed friday list four victims stemming back from 1998, including at least three months between the ages of 13 and 17. the victims are listed only by initials in the legal documents.

his next trial date is march 8. stay tuned...

i am not a conceited person.  i often wonder what people think when i post selfies.  let me tell you something: when to have been told u are fat, ugly, worthless, a cow, a whore, been the victim of sexual assault three times, survived domestic abuse, bullies (including a teacher telling me i was too fat to pursue dance), and breast cancer..you are left many times thinking that maybe you are really those things.  then i realize, again, that i am a fucking warrior...and i have every right to document times when i feel beautiful, alice, happy.  thats right ladies..#loveyourself, #metoo, #breastcancersurvivor, #domesticabusesurvivor

text:
sometimes you just need to... move! our traumas can often paralyse us, trap us in our 'safe space'. we stay nestled in our comfort zone. which served us so well. but its time to grow. don't stay stuck. move! walk, ground, earth, dance, run, stroll, trudge if you must, crawl if your that weary, but go forward, heal and grow and thrive! do not let the bad guys win. show courage, and brave strength by making a life you are proud of, content with and  in love with. do you! you've got this! do it you way, kindly but passionate and fierce!

text:
how vc-backed companies can mitigate #metoo risk | foley & lardner llp
#
this article originally appeared in law360 and is reprinted here with permission. the #metoo and time's up movements have placed boards of directors in the spotlight for how quickly and thoroughly they respond to allegations of sexual assault, sexual harassment and other improper behavior by founders, executives and employees. while public companies have had their share of struggles responding to such allegations, venture capital-backed startups, especially in their early stages, face unique challenges in addressing such allegations. for example, while well-established private or public companies have a succession plan and executives who can step in if a chief executive officer is placed on leave or resigns, early stage startups often do not. the founders are often central to the company’s survival and oftentimes are major stockholders as well. consequently, allegations against them may threaten the existence of the company, making it harder for a board to remove the individual for improper behavior. in light of this, there are proactive steps that venture capitalists can take to mitigate the risks posed by #metoo-related allegations. bases for liability victims of improper behavior and shareholders of companies where the behavior occurred can attempt to hold directors and officers, including venture capital representatives serving…

text:
#basta de abusos en el yoga 
el domingo 10/3 les invitamos a la plazoleta enrique garcía velloso, (frente al planetario de palermo) donde estaremos dando clases de yoga, de meditación, cantos de mantras, y abriremos un círculo de reflexión-información y contención con el objetivo de hacer visible los abusos y violencia que se dan también en el ámbito del yoga, donde falsos maestros de yoga utilizan esta poderosa herramienta, (es una practica milenaria creada para la unificación con el amor supremo o consciencia universal, que brinda amor y autoconocimiento) en beneficio de sus perversas personalidades, maltratando, humillando, menospreciando y abusando de sus alumnas/os. muchos de estos pseudo maestros tienen escuelas de yoga, otros forman “comunidades espirituales” pero todos son abusadores y explotadores, y con la mayoría aún no se ha hecho justicia. por eso juntos queremos visibilizar y concientizar para terminar con esto y que nos unamos en esta causa a una sola voz: basta de abusos en el yoga. para que todes podamos recibir y dar la sabiduría que conlleva la práctica del yoga. 
además de las actividades gratuitas habrá puestos de comida vegetariana, y artesanales, y se hará una rifa, con el objetivo de recaudar dinero para el pago de honorarios de la abogada de una de las afectadas. les esperamos! solo se suspende por lluvias. 
informes:
11-65050820 -whatsapp 
basta de abuso en el yoga - instagram 
cronograma: 
15:00 hs círculo de apertura. información, reflexión y contención. didácticas grupales.
16:00 hs kaoshikii: la danza de la expansión mental
16.30 a 18 clases de yoga 
18 hs mantras y meditación 
19hs. sorteo de la rifa, merienda y cierre. 
te esperamos! trae tu mat o manta y algo rico y vegetariano para compartir. también podes comprar en los puestos que habrá!

@yoguinisorganizadas @bastadeabusosenelyoga @vairayoga @cloledo @escueladetantraclasico @krishnapryadoula @mora.rubianes @revistacitrica @arg_india @argenindia #miracomonosponemos #mira #bastadeabusos #basta #noesno #yoga #yotecreo #yotecreo #yotecreohermana #unidas #unidasar #yoga #yogaworld #yoguinis #yoguini #metoo

when is the last time you struck up a conversation with a complete stranger sitting next to you? as i sat on a fully packed plane today, i could tell the person sitting next to me was struggling. i introduced myself and our conversation within a few moments turned to our personal lives. as i opened up about my marriage, divorce and coparenting situation, i saw a sense of relief on their face. we spent two hours talking about my last few years in dealing with addictions, anger, infidelity, and financial stresses. in the end, this stranger wasn’t so different from me. and my journey helped process some pain for them.
..
so the next time you meet a stranger, go out on a limb and share your story. you never know where it will take you. or them.
..
..
..

text: if you were a child and it happened to you, it is not your fault.  if it happened to you and you were/are an adult but not given a choice, it's not your fault.  as children, we look for adults and our "loved ones"  to have our backs.  to protect us and to make the best decisions for us.  sometimes they don't and that is not your fault. sometimes they don't look out for us simply because it happened to them too, and they don't know how to communicate it.  they're trauma has gone untreated. people they trusted to protect them and make the best decisions for them, did not.  they were wounded, undiagnosed, left untreated and they bled all over you.  guess what?  that is not your fault.  #generationalcurse #women #men #children #molestation #rape #incest #breakthecycle #trauma #masks #substanceusedisorder #prostitution #blackwoman #therapy #sexoffender #metoomovement #tell #unwarrantedsexualadvances #humantrafficking #metoo #humantraffickingawareness

text:
#jivedaily - r. kelly has been charged with 10 counts of aggravated criminal sexual abuse
.
.
.
r. kelly has been charged with 10 counts of aggravated criminal sexual abuse in cook county, illinois, the chicago sun-times and the chicago tribune report. according to the sun-times, a no-bail warrant for kelly’s arrest has been issued, and he is due in court on march 8.
.
.
.
at a press conference today (february 22), cook county state’s attorney kimberly foxx detailed the charges against r. kelly. aggravated criminal sexual abuse is a class 2 with a sentencing range of three-to-seven years per count. foxx said, “we anticipate that mr. kelly will appear in bond court tomorrow afternoon.” find the press conference below. according to kimberly foxx, the first victim (whose initials are h.w.) said she was involved in incidents with r. kelly between may 26, 1998 and may 25, 1999 when she was under the age of 17 and kelly was more than five years older than her. a grand jury returned an indictment against kelly on four counts of aggravated criminal sexual abuse of h.w.
.
.
.
yesterday, two more women stepped forward with more allegations of sexual misconduct levied against kelly. one of the women, latrice, said she was 16 years old when kelly had sexual intercourse with her after giving her drugs and alcohol. the other woman, rochelle, alleged that kelly exposed himself to the two of them and asked the then-teenage girls for a threesome.
.
.
.

text:
listen to black women. listen to women of color. listen to the trans community. listen to women in poverty. listen to survivors.
•
“the ‘me too.’ movement was founded in 2006 to help survivors of sexual violence, particularly black women and girls, and other young women of color from low wealth communities, find pathways to healing. our vision from the beginning was to address both the dearth in resources for survivors of sexual violence and to build a community of advocates, driven by survivors, who will be at the forefront of creating solutions to interrupt sexual violence in their communities... our goal is also to reframe and expand the global conversation around sexual violence to speak to the needs of a broader spectrum of survivors. young people, queer, trans, and disabled folks, black women and girls, and all communities of color. we want perpetrators to be held accountable and we want strategies implemented to sustain long term, systemic change.... tarana burke began ‘me too’ with young black women and girls from low wealth communities. she developed culturally-informed curriculum to discuss sexual violence within the black community and in society at large. similarly, the ‘me too’ movement seeks to support folks working within their communities to attend to the specific needs of their community/communities, i.e. supporting disabled trans survivors of color working to lead and craft events/toolkits/etc. with other disabled trans survivors. together, we can uplift and support each other to strengthen a global movement to interrupt sexual violence.” ~metoomvmt.org
•
i created this #metoo poster for the grand central library-posters for a cause presents: a call to action: creative messaging for social change and it was hanging in the library from november 15, 2018 to january 11, 2019.
•

quote: taran burke

text:
《乳房》the udder - marianna simnett, 2014

這部戲劇性的影片激發了一個於英國修適士郡生活與在製奶農莊工作的一家人的精彩演出。牛隻平靜地前往採奶地，無聲地任由周圍機構的擺佈，亦會令人想到我們的身體與無所不在的科技的關係。幼女臉上的唇膏有人造的性質，同樣，科技的無處不在意味着，「有機」這個概念得到了它們的補充或替代，已經難稱自然或純潔。

the work incites startling performances from a family who live and work on a dairy farm in sussex in the uk. the cows proceeding placidly to the milking station, mutely acquiescing to the surrounding apparatus, also invoke our bodies’ relationship to technology which increasingly envelops us. just as there is artifice to the red lipstick on the little girl’s face, so too does the pervasiveness of technology imply that the notion of the organic is supplanted or supplemented by that which cannot easily be
considered natural or pure.

表演社會：性別的暴力 performing society: the violence of gender 
16.02.2019 – 28.04.2019

法蘭克福現代藝術美術館呈獻

presented by museum mmk für moderne kunst, frankfurt
am main

susanne pfeffer策展 curated by susanne pfeffer 
部份展覽只供十八歲或以上人士參觀 *part of the exhibition is restricted to persons aged 18 and above only

no word of a lie this year has been tough for me already. continuing to work on myself, loving myself and making some changes and different choices. life doesnt feel too good for me right now. god promises that: "and we know that all things work together for good to them that love god, to them who are the called according to his purpose." roman's 8:28.

so this is keeping me sane and hopeful. feelings are temporary, seasons are temporary. remember 🤗 that.

still a queen 👑✊.

text:
you have the power!

dedicated to  @prettyboyramon

pain is deep rooted and requires support, love, and time for it to fade away. although, when someone takes the pain and glorifies it for their own gain hurts and causes those emotions you've laid to rest to come back from the dead.

however, i am here to say this, "don't let one person who is obviously in pain cause you to retreat. the naysayers will always try to bring you down or keep you in the dark, but one thing i do know; whatever's in the dark will eventually come to light.

stand up and be heard.  i almost lost my voice because my integrity and sincerity were questioned. however, in my case, the joke is on the person because their negativity towards me only empowered and encouraged me to have a louder voice.  #metoo

text:
​​#историичитателей

мне ещё нет 30 лет. вышла замуж, когда училась на третьем курсе престижного вуза, за парня из типичной узбекской семьи. сразу после свадьбы свекровь сказала мне, что она не хотела женить сына на меня, так как моя специальность не соответствовала ее ожиданиям. она хотела келинку с медицинским образованием (хотя бы медсестру), а я была, видите ли, студенткой юридического института. но ее сыну я сильно понравилась во время учрашув. он сильно настаивал на том, чтобы жениться на мне, и она еле согласилась. она говорила, что я не соответствую ее идеалам. “вот многих девушек, хороших и красивых, я показывала своему сыну, но он почему-то выбрал тебя. я не понимаю, что он в тебе нашел. мой сын такой классный, много зарабатывает. ты должна соответствовать ему во всем” и т.д., и т.п. 
я сама тоже не хотела замуж, хотела еще учиться, но моим родителям пришлись по душе сваты, и чуть ли не силой меня выдали замуж. с того дня у меня все опустело к новому дому. к свекрови я охладела, но, не подавая виду, делала все дела по дому: готовила, стирала, убирала, каждый день принимала тоннами гостей – при моей учебе (на третьем курсе было нааамного труднее учиться) и при том, что я была беременна. но свекровь моя была вечно недовольна мной, говорила всякие гадости про меня моему мужу, чтобы поссорить нас (жутко ревновала сына), скандалила. когда родился мой первый ребенок, оклеветала меня и чуть ли не выгнала из дома. 
я ушла, и моя мама вернула меня туда через 4 дня. потом еще скандалы из-за всякой ерунды, ни одна неделя не проходила без инцидентов. я родителям ничего об этом не говорила, так как они у меня старые и больные. дома тоже не сахар, домой не хотела и вынуждена была ради сына все терпеть и жить там. 
в прошлом году женился младший брат мужа на медсестре. и что вы думаете, как она живет?! она живет просто роскошно со сравнинию со мной! целыми днями спит, по дому ничего не делает, не готовит, не убирает. но в почете всегда и везде. она не из богатой семьи, но у нее прописка городская, и если снесут дом, в котором она прописана, ей может достаться дом. свекровь на это расчитывает.
name: Не молчи

мне ещё нет 30 лет. вышла замуж, когда училась на третьем курсе престижного вуза, за парня из типичной узбекской семьи. сразу после свадьбы свекровь сказала мне, что она не хотела женить сына на меня, так как моя специальность не соответствовала ее ожиданиям. она хотела келинку с медицинским образованием (хотя бы медсестру), а я была, видите ли, студенткой юридического института. но ее сыну я сильно понравилась во время учрашув. он сильно настаивал на том, чтобы жениться на мне, и она еле согласилась. она говорила, что я не соответствую ее идеалам. “вот многих девушек, хороших и красивых, я показывала своему сыну, но он почему-то выбрал тебя. я не понимаю, что он в тебе нашел. мой сын такой классный, много зарабатывает. ты должна соответствовать ему во всем” и т.д., и т.п. 
я сама тоже не хотела замуж, хотела еще учиться, но моим родителям пришлись по душе сваты, и чуть ли не силой меня выдали замуж. с того дня у меня все опустело к новому дому. к свекрови я охладела, но, не подавая виду, делала все дела по дому: готовила, стирала, убирала, каждый день принимала тоннами гостей – при моей учебе (на третьем курсе было нааамного труднее учиться) и при том, что я была беременна. но свекровь моя была вечно недовольна мной, говорила всякие гадости про меня моему мужу, чтобы поссорить нас (жутко ревновала сына), скандалила. когда родился мой первый ребенок, оклеветала меня и чуть ли не выгнала из дома. 
я ушла, и моя мама вернула меня туда через 4 дня. потом еще скандалы из-за всякой ерунды, ни одна неделя не проходила без инцидентов. я родителям ничего об этом не говорила, так как они у меня старые и больные. дома тоже не сахар, домой не хотела и вынуждена была ради сына все терпеть и жить там. 
в прошлом году женился младший брат мужа на медсестре. и что вы думаете, как она живет?! она живет просто роскошно со сравнинию со мной! целыми днями спит, по дому ничего не делает, не готовит, не убирает. но в почете всегда и везде. она не из богатой семьи, но у нее прописка городская, и если снесут дом, в котором она прописана, ей может достаться дом. свекровь на это расчитывает.
stop_filter_tweet: ​​сториичитателей мне ещё нет 30 лет . вышла замуж , когда училась на третьем курсе престижного вуза , за парня из типичной узбекской семьи . сразу после свадьбы свекровь сказала мне , что она не хотела женить сына на меня , так как моя специальность не соответствовала ее ожиданиям . она хотела келинку с медицинским образованием ( хотя бы медсестру ) , а я была , видите ли , студенткой юридического института . но ее сыну я сильно понравилась во время учрашув . он сильно настаивал на том , чтобы жениться на мне , и она еле согласилась . она говорила , что я не соответствую ее идеалам . “ вот многих девушек , хороших и красивых , я показывала своему сыну , но он почему-то выбрал тебя . я не понимаю , что он в тебе нашел . мой сын такой классный , много зарабатывает . ты должна соответствовать ему во всем ” и т.д. , и т.п . я сама тоже не хотела замуж , хотела еще учиться , но моим родителям пришлись по душе сваты , и чуть ли не силой меня выдали замуж . с того дня у меня все опустело к новому дому . к свекрови я охладела , но , не подавая виду , делала все дела по дому : готовила , стирала , убирала , каждый день принимала тоннами гостей – при моей учебе ( на третьем курсе было нааамного труднее учиться ) и при том , что я была беременна . но свекровь моя была вечно недовольна мной , говорила всякие гадости про меня моему мужу , чтобы поссорить нас ( жутко ревновала сына ) , скандалила . когда родился мой первый ребенок , оклеветала меня и чуть ли не выгнала из дома . я ушла , и моя мама вернула меня туда через 4 дня . потом еще скандалы из-за всякой ерунды , ни одна неделя не проходила без инцидентов . я родителям ничего об этом не говорила , так как они у меня старые и больные . дома тоже не сахар , домой не хотела и вынуждена была ради сына все терпеть и жить там . в прошлом году женился младший брат мужа на медсестре . и что вы думаете , как она живет ? ! она живет просто роскошно со сравнинию со мной ! целыми днями спит , по дому ничего не делает , не готовит , не убирает . но в почете всегда и везде . она не из богатой семьи , но у нее прописка городская , и если снесут дом , в котором она прописана , ей может достаться дом . свекровь на это расчитывает .

text:
apapun gaya dan ekspresimu, kamu berhak aman dan bebas dari kekerasan seksual..!! —————— lemahnya perlindungan hukum atas kekerasan seksual tentu menjadi penghambat dalam pelaporan dan penanganan korban. belum lagi cara pandangan yang masih sering menyalahkan korban justru membuat pembatasan ruang gerak tidak ditujukan pada pelaku melainkan pada korban seperti contoh: adanya jam malam untuk perempuan, aturan berpakaian, cara berperilaku, bertutur serta kenyamanan berekspresi lainnya. hingga saat ini belum ada peringatan dan tindakan tegas bagi pelaku, sehingga berdampak pada pembiaraan kasus kekerasan seksual yang membuat korban semakin diam dan malu untuk melaporkan.

pelaku kekerasan seksual bisa siapa saja. bisa dari orang yang sama sekali tidak kita kenal atau bahkan orang yang justru dekat dengan kita, seperti teman sebaya, teman satu komunitas, pacar, pengajar dan sebagainya. kita tahu bahwa yang menjadi korban kekerasan seksual tidak selalu perempuan, korbannya juga bisa laki-laki. oleh karenanya laki-laki harus turut mengambil peran dari perlawanan terhadap perjuangan untuk menghapuskan kekerasan seksual.

apa sih manfaatnya dengan kita turut ambil peran dalam
penghapusan kekerasan seksual?

kita dapat memastikan terciptanya ruang aman, nyaman, bebas berekspresi dan bebas dari kekerasan seksual, agar orang-orang terdekat dan teman-teman kita tidak menjadi korban selanjutnya. 
karena kasus-kasus pelecehan dan kekerasan seksual dapat terjadi pada siapa saja dan di mana saja, oleh karena itu perlawanan terhadapnya pun harus hadir dari siapa saja dan di mana saja semakin banyak teman-teman yang turut bersuara, maka semakin besar pula perlawanan terhadap kekerasan seksual tersebut.

text:
внутреннее равновесие
🌿🌿🌿🌿🌿
сколько бы раз я не говорила себе:" не делай то, что тебе  априори не нравится", но кажется танцевать на поле граблей-мое призвание.
🌿🌿🌿🌿🌿
как не странно ща внешней оболочкой  скрывается целый прекрасный мир. погода в котором зависит от твоих чувств.
радость- солнечный теплый день.
восторг- раннее утро, восход с лёгким туманом,когда не знаешь что дальше, но тебе уже безумно нравится и волнует.
грусть- противный, мелкий осенний дождь, тот ,который не любит ни кто. он капает на твои нервы и вгоняет в депрессию.
а какие катаклизмы может вызвать злость или ненависть...
люби свой мир, иногда поливай, радуйся рассветам, но не забывай и про солнечный свет.

#янебоюсьсказать #студент  #metoo #mylife

text:
"in #meeshashafi's case, and also in #metoo's case, we can see how power works, how it silences. meesha was subjected to personal hate and professional vitriol, effectively shut down and forced to retreat. #alizafar's defamation suit set a precedent so students and teenagers, who were taking to social media to name and shame, ended up deleting their testimonies for the fear of lawsuits. out of the four popular men who have been named after ali zafar - faisal edhi, taimur rahman, junaid akram and #feica - only feica's case has been followed up. but nothing has come of it, and, meanwhile, the rest move unhindered. the entire leftist brigade has descended in the defence of #faisaledhi, #taimurrahman has ignored the complaints and #junaidakram has tweeted that he will take his accusers to court. the women who named these men are facing intense cyberbullying while the men are weaponising silence itself: to quote ali zafar, "silence is not an option." but, unlike ali zafar, those of us who have actually experienced silencing, know that it works like a pressure cooker - at some point it erupts. we only have to look around: #metoo has made it impossible to sit in a gathering of women and not have the discussion veer towards sexual abuse; all our conversations are about the latest person named, wherever in the world, about our personal stories of survival, about how we feel, what we fear. we do not always agree about the politics of #metoo and its strategies, but we are collectively labouring under its weight" — @journalofsad // @girlsatdhabas — #meeshashafi, raising her voice to a new pitch —@herald_magazine #lahooti
#lahootimelo #lahootimelo2019 #metoopakistan #odetowomen 📸 @thenarrativekhi

text:
i was very young when all of this took place, so i only every really knew what the media was touting and what the grown ups were laughing about. so glad i got a deeper look into this whole thing this week. 
if you’ve got a few days to carve out for this 4 part docuseries, it is a really eloquently and artfully pieced together look into the pre-#metoo discussion of domestic abuse and women’s rights/justice in a male-centric world and a tabloid hungry nation. and how that has (and/or hasn’t) evolved over the years.
seriously, it’s worth the watch. plenty of talking/yelling at the tv moments. at least, that was my experience. 
airforce amy summarized it best: “they can cut a million clits off in africa and nobody hears a word. you cut one dick off and the whole fuckin country stops.”
#lorenabobbitt

if you’ve got a few days to carve out for this 4 part docuseries, it is a really eloquently and artfully pieced together look into the pre-#metoo discussion of domestic abuse and women’s rights/justice in a male-centric world and a tabloid hungry nation. and how that has (and/or hasn’t) evolved over the years.
seriously, it’s worth the watch. plenty of talking/yelling at the tv moments. at least, that was my experience. 
airforce amy summarized it best: “they can cut a million clits off in africa and nobody hears a word. you cut one dick off and the whole fuckin country stops.”
#lorenabobbitt

text:
this is my life now 🙄
nogle starter dagen med lækker morgenmad... jeg starter dagen med morphin...
før alt det her var jeg en der dårlig ville tage en panodil. jeg var stor modstander (for mig selv) for at skulle tage piller hvis jeg på nogen måde kunne lade være. jeg drak ikke alkohol, tog ikke stoffer, levede kostmæssigt meget rent, dyrkede dagligt yoga, mediterede og var idet hele taget meget god mod mig selv. problemet var at jeg levede med ptsd (uden at vide det) som jeg havde haft i årevis og ikke fået behandling for. jeg har været psykisk syg on/off,)det meste af mit liv men kun blevet symptom behandlet. til trods for at jeg ærligt havde fortalt diverse læger og terapeuter hvad jeg havde været udsat for i barndommen (det i mit voksenliv kom først frem senere) så var der ingen der overvejede om alle mine symptomer kunne stamme fra ubehandlede traumer, dvs senfølger. og derfor blev jeg bare mere og mere ødelagt.
jeg deler min historie herinde fordi jeg inderligt ønsker og håber at hvis der sidder nogle derude som har været igennem nogle voldsomme ting at i så vil insisterer på at få den rette hjælp. ubehandlede traumer sætter sig i kroppen som ptsd og kan udviklede sig til kroniske sygdomme som eks dem jeg har (fibromyalgi og pnes) det kan også komme til udtryk på alle mulige andre måder. det vigtige er at lytte til faresignalerne og tage dem alvorligt. for har du været udsat for traumer så er det klart at du er påvirket, at du kæmper, at du blir syg hele tiden. men du behøver ikke gå det igennem alene. og du har ret til at få hjælp til at bearbejde det. du har ret til at få hjælp til at lære at leve med dine traumatiske oplevelser. ❤️ 🙏 #yournotalone #etlivmedptsd #senfølger #livetmedpnes #fibromyalgi #findyourstrenght #findyourinspirations #metoo #gethelp #knowyourrights #rækud

（續上）......andréa bescond之面對自己，尚在於將此經歷拍成作品傳揚後世。於電影壓軸一幕，成年版的odette卒之鼓起勇氣，打開那扇令人不安的門，與性侵現場裡昔日的小女孩odette對話；這個「超現實」安排，無疑是她的終極釋懷。的確，較諸父母、朋友和戀人，odette要真正突破自己的話，就必須直面自己的過去。這一幕裡，成人odette說自己一直將小女孩odette遺在洗手間，現在則要帶她走出枷鎖－－這一種釋懷，某程度是電影最最最催淚的部分。畢竟，小女孩odette豈非一直望眼欲穿，希望有人帶她走出深淵？而成年後的odette，亦一直希望有人幫助當年的自己，包括由她一手幫助性侵受害者......的確，這一幕存在雙重意義，andréa bescond牽著小女孩挺身而出，實也象徵她想牽著其他性侵受害者挺身而出－－她要拯救的，不止於戲裡的小女孩odette，而且還有世上千千萬萬個odette！片末交代歐洲的性侵數字，正正與此主題互相對照。
～
說了許多「以戲載道」的點讚位，不得不談的尚有上文一再提及的「現實」性質與「超現實」性質。
～
odette的人設無疑很「貼地」，例如愛好畫畫，又以舞蹈為目標，包括父母都想培育她當舞蹈員－－試問，這不是像極了許多小女孩的現況？的確，無論你我，任何人均可能是#metoo受害者。有人說，女孩版odette比成人版odette更加成功，理由是前者嬌嫩欲滴，後者不單被嚴重比下去，其風格也太過粗獷、太過狂野，以致不太討好觀眾云云......必須強調，如前所述，andréa bescond正正就是#metoo受害者，試問由她出演豈不順理成章？她的人物設定又哪來「不現實」？更重要是，不要以為只有外表討好的，才會淪為被性侵對象。君不見香港法庭新聞，許多弱者包括智障人士恰恰最易遭殃，而愈是弱勢者所受傷害亦恐愈大......事實上，odette的人生變得「墮落」，豈不進一步凸顯性侵對她的負面打擊？難道成人版odette繼續亭亭玉立、以至人格完美，這才叫「正常」、電影才「吸引」嗎？《說不出口的遊戲》正好道盡「現實」的一切不幸。
～
的確，不跳優雅的芭蕾舞，而跳著重情緒宣洩的現代舞及街舞，也是odette人設的一大成功之處；較諸平鋪直述純粹以對白交代，廣佈於電影不同階段的「超現實」舞蹈「突入」，便把odette當時心境展現得淋漓盡致，描寫感染力因而大大強化昇華。另外，她跟心理醫生等不時「突入」「超現實」的回憶片段，相關鏡頭運用不僅增添了電影玩味，odette於此「案發現場」和「假想空間」的「事後檢討」，同樣地，較諸刻板地透過旁白或回到醫生診所呈現，緊扣現場的張力與「貼地」感覺亦肯定強大得多。當然，凡此種種，更旨在鋪排最終壓軸「odette與odette對話」的重頭戲；倘無前面的「超現實」「前菜」，觀眾實不易接受及品嚐這幕「超現實」「主菜」。
～
筆者心想，如果電影結局再加一幕「超現實」情節，讓成人odette重返電影開初的第一幕，由她喝停gilbert帶走女孩odette進入洗手間－－如此的話，電影會否更加完美？然而，筆者很快就自我推翻了。因為，本片不在追求完美，而在告訴大家如何面對不完美，正如#metoo所著重的是舉報罪行，andréa bescond之所以拍攝本片也由於她已撫平昔日痛痕。雖然，假使odette父母事前有效關愛女兒，任何不幸誠有可能完全避免，電影也告誡現實中的父母要「多聽子女心底話」；不過，這裡的「多聽子女心底話」，亦更多在於為子女坦誠相向創造更佳條件，好使子女向父母道盡困擾、繼而讓父母解決子女困擾。透過本片，相信andréa bescond所希望傳遞的第一個願望，是鼓勵一眾性侵受害人挺身而出，即針對「事已至此」的人而言；第二個願望，才是鼓勵大家多關愛身邊人，毋使不幸悲劇一再發生、一再困住受害者。
～
無論如何，怎樣令「說不出口的遊戲」「說出口來」，包括由家長到社會怎樣營造「說得出口」的環境，無疑乃是#metoo精神的最佳體現。（劇透版二之二）
～
http://www.thinkhk.com/article/2019-02/22/33130.html
～
（影評全文，請瀏覽思考香港或facebook專頁）

stop_filter_tweet: 【說不出口的遊戲。影評】真人真事！有血有淚！來讓一切說得出口！ 李美 ～ （注意，以下完全劇透，有雷） ～ （續上） ... ... andréa bescond之面對自己，尚在於將此經歷拍成作品傳揚後世。於電影壓軸一幕，成年版的odette卒之鼓起勇氣，打開那扇令人不安的門，與性侵現場裡昔日的小女孩odette對話；這個「超現實」安排，無疑是她的終極釋懷。的確，較諸父母、朋友和戀人，odette要真正突破自己的話，就必須直面自己的過去。這一幕裡，成人odette說自己一直將小女孩odette遺在洗手間，現在則要帶她走出枷鎖－－這一種釋懷，某程度是電影最最最催淚的部分。畢竟，小女孩odette豈非一直望眼欲穿，希望有人帶她走出深淵？而成年後的odette，亦一直希望有人幫助當年的自己，包括由她一手幫助性侵受害者 ... ... 的確，這一幕存在雙重意義，andréa bescond牽著小女孩挺身而出，實也象徵她想牽著其他性侵受害者挺身而出－－她要拯救的，不止於戲裡的小女孩odette，而且還有世上千千萬萬個odette！片末交代歐洲的性侵數字，正正與此主題互相對照。 ～ 說了許多「以戲載道」的點讚位，不得不談的尚有上文一再提及的「現實」性質與「超現實」性質。 ～ odette的人設無疑很「貼地」，例如愛好畫畫，又以舞蹈為目標，包括父母都想培育她當舞蹈員－－試問，這不是像極了許多小女孩的現況？的確，無論你我，任何人均可能是 bescond正正就是etoo受害者，試問由她出演豈不順理成章？她的人物設定又哪來「不現實」？更重要是，不要以為只有外表討好的，才會淪為被性侵對象。君不見香港法庭新聞，許多弱者包括智障人士恰恰最易遭殃，而愈是弱勢者所受傷害亦恐愈大 ... ... 事實上，odette的人生變得「墮落」，豈不進一步凸顯性侵對她的負面打擊？難道成人版odette繼續亭亭玉立、以至人格完美，這才叫「正常」、電影才「吸引」嗎？《說不出口的遊戲》正好道盡「現實」的一切不幸。 ～ 的確，不跳優雅的芭蕾舞，而跳著重情緒宣洩的現代舞及街舞，也是odette人設的一大成功之處；較諸平鋪直述純粹以對白交代，廣佈於電影不同階段的「超現實」舞蹈「突入」，便把odette當時心境展現得淋漓盡致，描寫感染力因而大大強化昇華。另外，她跟心理醫生等不時「突入」「超現實」的回憶片段，相關鏡頭運用不僅增添了電影玩味，odette於此「案發現場」和「假想空間」的「事後檢討」，同樣地，較諸刻板地透過旁白或回到醫生診所呈現，緊扣現場的張力與「貼地」感覺亦肯定強大得多。當然，凡此種種，更旨在鋪排最終壓軸「odette與odette對話」的重頭戲；倘無前面的「超現實」「前菜」，觀眾實不易接受及品嚐這幕「超現實」「主菜」。 ～ 筆者心想，如果電影結局再加一幕「超現實」情節，讓成人odette重返電影開初的第一幕，由她喝停gilbe帶走女孩odette進入洗手間－－如此的話，電影會否更加完美？然而，筆者很快就自我推翻了。因為，本片不在追求完美，而在告訴大家如何面對不完美，正如 bescond之所以拍攝本片也由於她已撫平昔日痛痕。雖然，假使odette父母事前有效關愛女兒，任何不幸誠有可能完全避免，電影也告誡現實中的父母要「多聽子女心底話」；不過，這裡的「多聽子女心底話」，亦更多在於為子女坦誠相向創造更佳條件，好使子女向父母道盡困擾、繼而讓父母解決子女困擾。透過本片，相信andréa bescond所希望傳遞的第一個願望，是鼓勵一眾性侵受害人挺身而出，即針對「事已至此」的人而言；第二個願望，才是鼓勵大家多關愛身邊人，毋使不幸悲劇一再發生、一再困住受害者。 ～ 無論如何，怎樣令「說不出口的遊戲」「說出口來」，包括由家長到社會怎樣營造「說得出口」的環境，無疑乃是etoo精神的最佳體現。（劇透版二之二） ～ ～ （影評全文，請瀏覽思考香港或facebook專頁） ～ 美 影 不出口的遊戲 能說的遊戲 瘙癢 ittletickles hetickling hedanceofwrath ndréabescond yrillemairesse arolefranck ricmétayer etoo ovie

text:
r&b star r. kelly has been charged with 10 counts of aggravated criminal sex abuse, at least some involving minors, a cook county court official said friday. .
the embattled singer — dogged for decades by sexual abuse allegations involving underage women — has a court date scheduled for march 8 in chicago, where he resides, the official told afp.
.
on thursday, there was a fresh addition to a slew of lurid allegations against the r&b superstar when two more women accused him of sexually assaulting them as teens.
.
latresa scaff, 40, and rochelle washington, 39, told journalists in new york they met kelly at a show’s after-party in baltimore in the 1990s, giving them alcohol and drugs before cornering them in his hotel room and demanding sex.
.
they were unable to pinpoint the year of the concert but said it was either 1995 or 1996, adding kelly’s security picked them out of the arena’s crowd.
.
at the after-party, they were given cocaine, marijuana and alcohol and invited to kelly’s hotel room, according to scaff, who said a man with a walkie-talkie told them: “r. kelly is getting ready to enter the room. pull up your dresses.”
.
the artist, now 52, then came in wearing a shirt and jeans but with his genitals exposed.
.
washington refused his advances and hid in the bathroom, but scaff gave him oral sex and then had intercourse with him, “even though i did not have the capacity to consent,” she said.
.
 without providing further detail, allred said some women she is representing fear video or audio recordings of their relations with kelly may be circulating.
.
for decades the artist — real name robert sylvester kelly — has faced lawsuits and accusations over child pornography, sex with minors, operating a sex cult and sexual battery.
.
“you have nowhere to run and nowhere to hide,” allred said, referring to kelly. “you have been able to get away with your predatory misconduct for far too long. (afp)

the embattled singer — dogged for decades by sexual abuse allegations involving underage women — has a court date scheduled for march 8 in chicago, where he resides, the official told afp.
.
on thursday, there was a fresh addition to a slew of lurid allegations against the r&b superstar when two more women accused him of sexually assaulting them as teens.
.
latresa scaff, 40, and rochelle washington, 39, told journalists in new york they met kelly at a show’s after-party in baltimore in the 1990s, giving them alcohol and drugs before cornering them in his hotel room and demanding sex.
.
they were unable to pinpoint the year of the concert but said it was either 1995 or 1996, adding kelly’s security picked them out of the arena’s crowd.
.
at the after-party, they were given cocaine, marijuana and alcohol and invited to kelly’s hotel room, according to scaff, who said a man with a walkie-talkie told them: “r. kelly is getting ready to enter the room. pull up your dresses.”
.
the artist, now 52, then came in wearing a shirt and jeans but with his genitals exposed.
.
washington refused his advances and hid in the bathroom, but scaff gave him oral sex and then had intercourse with him, “even though i did not have the capacity to consent,” she said.
.
 without providing further detail, allred said some women she is representing fear video or audio recordings of their relations with kelly may be circulating.
.
for decades the artist — real name robert sylvester kelly — has faced lawsuits and accusations over child pornography, sex with minors, operating a sex cult and sexual battery.
.
“you have nowhere to run and nowhere to hide,” allred said, referring to kelly. “you have been able to get away with your predatory misconduct for far too long. (afp)

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
♡2019年2月23日♡
5:00 トイレに入ったら隣の502号室もトイレの音がする。しばらく治っていたのに復活した。
相変わらず。
それ以降も外出する準備をしてる7:00代から屋根裏がうるさく、
11:00 明らかに故意に叩いてる音。
むこのそう近畿住研は心を入れ替える気もなく、嫌がらせは続く。
慣れたとはいえ一年以上続いて精神的にはキツイ。起きて何かをしていると気に入らないらしく屋根裏を叩く。
だから昼間しんどい時は寝るようにしている。
好きで夜型になってるわけではない。
日中は工事業者のフリして騒音を立てられたり
しんどいので、騒がしい昼に寝て、朝早くならそれほどの音にはしないので朝早めに起きている。
朝でもミシミシと言うような音はするが。
むこのそう近畿住研。
やってる事ヤンマーと変わらない。
と言うか、全く同じなので無関係とは言わせない。
12:15 脱衣所の洗面台の鏡を拭いた。見やすくなったかな？むこのそう近畿住研。
会社でも同じ、私が鏡を使わないと席に戻ったら周りの社員がイラついて騒音をたてる。
家と会社とこんなに同じ。
同じ人の考えだと思うのは私だけかな。

たかこは自分で問題を作っておいて「それは病気のせいでそんな事はしていない、気のせいで今は病気を治すのに専念してください」という言葉が返ってきた。
アンタが原因をつくったんやと言いたい
それどころか私を否定する内容の書面。
何も知らなかったくせに知ったような文面で
ヤンマーの自作自演と訴えている事まで知ってるはずなのに揚げ足を取って私の人格否定。
これも自作自演のヤンマーと同じではないか？

家族の縁は戸籍で切ることはできないが、向こうから切られたようなもの
宣戦布告された気分
そういう人間とわかっていたけど、私と娘の人生がかかったこの時期に「私の娘が心配で」と偽善者ぶる
知らない人から見たらそう見えるだろう
でも本当の事を知ってる人は私がもう家族として名乗らないで欲しいという理由はわかってくれると思う。
初めの一回でちゃんとした回答をしてくれると少し期待したがやっぱり人間の性格は変わらない。森岡と同じ認めても大した被害にならないものだけだろう、
今日も寝ていたらたかこが住んでる下からコンコン音がする。
昔からなので驚きはしないが
相変わらずで
・
・
もうすぐ#andmore の抽選…
当たる気がしない…
なにかの力で…
#untitled もそうだったように…
去年10月もそうだったように… ・
・
【追加】
この前の投稿の手紙という映画を見てください。
大元を黙らせない限り引っ越しても永遠です。
社内だけ、マンション内だけなら
それで解決するかもしれませんが
これだけ広まった今はなおさら。
それからまた返事を^_^
【追加②】
むこのそう近畿住研は土日の対応も嫌がる、契約書に書いてる事でも「それは実費で」というケチケチ業者です
自費でそんな大それたお金のかかる事しないです。
出資者がいる。
ということは…わかりますよね^_^
・

やってる事ヤンマーと変わらない。
と言うか、全く同じなので無関係とは言わせない。
12:15 脱衣所の洗面台の鏡を拭いた。見やすくなったかな？むこのそう近畿住研。
会社でも同じ、私が鏡を使わないと席に戻ったら周りの社員がイラついて騒音をたてる。
家と会社とこんなに同じ。
同じ人の考えだと思うのは私だけかな。

たかこは自分で問題を作っておいて「それは病気のせいでそんな事はしていない、気のせいで今は病気を治すのに専念してください」という言葉が返ってきた。
アンタが原因をつくったんやと言いたい
それどころか私を否定する内容の書面。
何も知らなかったくせに知ったような文面で
ヤンマーの自作自演と訴えている事まで知ってるはずなのに揚げ足を取って私の人格否定。
これも自作自演のヤンマーと同じではないか？

家族の縁は戸籍で切ることはできないが、向こうから切られたようなもの
宣戦布告された気分
そういう人間とわかっていたけど、私と娘の人生がかかったこの時期に「私の娘が心配で」と偽善者ぶる
知らない人から見たらそう見えるだろう
でも本当の事を知ってる人は私がもう家族として名乗らないで欲しいという理由はわかってくれると思う。
初めの一回でちゃんとした回答をしてくれると少し期待したがやっぱり人間の性格は変わらない。森岡と同じ認めても大した被害にならないものだけだろう、
今日も寝ていたらたかこが住んでる下からコンコン音がする。
昔からなので驚きはしないが
相変わらずで
・
・

当たる気がしない…
なにかの力で…

去年10月もそうだったように… ・
・

それで解決するかもしれませんが
これだけ広まった今はなおさら。
それからまた返事を^_^

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytica $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
for years, americans have shrugged their shoulders over nsa surveillance and government access to digital data and said, “i don’t care; i have nothing to hide.” now they are starting to see that maybe they do have something to hide. they are starting to understand that their own preferences and those of their friends and family can be hoovered up and stored in perpetuity and fed through algorithms to produce manipulative messaging intended to move beliefs and influence actions.

although regulators and state attorneys general are launching investigations, the real hammer will be the market. whether it is facebook, twitter, or some other social media platform, when users start to realize that the data they are sharing may be used against them or cause them to lose control over their beliefs or be manipulated, they will begin to shut off. if the company can’t be trusted with personal data, users simply will not use that platform and advertisers will go elsewhere.

roger mcnamee, mark zuckerberg’s long-time mentor, saw the risk early on and tried to get facebook executives to manage it, but his warnings fell on deaf ears.  in an interview with christiane amanpour, mcnamee said that in october 2016, he personally warned zuckerberg and sheryl sandberg of the magnitude of the risk, but failed to get their attention. according to mcnamee, facebook’s leaders kept arguing that facebook is a platform company, not a media company and “we’re not responsible for what third parties do.” mcnamee warned them then, - you have 1.7 billion members and if they decide you are responsible, it won’t matter what the law says.

text_retweet:
rp @jessyforthevoiceless 
graphic footage - cows can only produce milk after giving birth, so dairy farms have to constantly forcibly impregnate the cows. 
as a result, many baby calves are born. 
since male calves will never produce milk, they are of no use to a dairy farm. ▪ 
some farms let the calves live for a few months in order to slaughter them for veal.
an analysis shows that it can cost a farmer up to £30 per calf to sell it on for beef or veal, while 'early disposal' costs just £9.
▪ 
as seen, the workers shoot days-old calves in the head, then leave them to bleed in a mass grave. 
the worker doesn’t even make any special effort to shoot the calves in a way that will deliver a quick death. 
in addition, each calf only gets one bullet in order to save costs.
(this footage is from a dairy farm in florida).
but make no mistake, this happens all over the world.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
reposted from @lebanesevegans - just a normal and legal practice under the umbrella of “humane” slaughter. you can stop this by not buying dairy anymore. alternatives are everywhere.
.

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
for years, americans have shrugged their shoulders over nsa surveillance and government access to digital data and said, “i don’t care; i have nothing to hide.” now they are starting to see that maybe they do have something to hide. they are starting to understand that their own preferences and those of their friends and family can be hoovered up and stored in perpetuity and fed through algorithms to produce manipulative messaging intended to move beliefs and influence actions.

although regulators and state attorneys general are launching investigations, the real hammer will be the market. whether it is facebook, twitter, or some other social media platform, when users start to realize that the data they are sharing may be used against them or cause them to lose control over their beliefs or be manipulated, they will begin to shut off. if the company can’t be trusted with personal data, users simply will not use that platform and advertisers will go elsewhere.

roger mcnamee, mark zuckerberg’s long-time mentor, saw the risk early on and tried to get facebook executives to manage it, but his warnings fell on deaf ears.  in an interview with christiane amanpour, mcnamee said that in october 2016, he personally warned zuckerberg and sheryl sandberg of the magnitude of the risk, but failed to get their attention. according to mcnamee, facebook’s leaders kept arguing that facebook is a platform company, not a media company and “we’re not responsible for what third parties do.” mcnamee warned them then, - you have 1.7 billion members and if they decide you are responsible, it won’t matter what the law says.

jody westby
forbes

text:
#art // lucretia _______________
📍: rome, italy
✍: @artnet + @wikipedia
📸: @classicartworks
•
according to roman tradition, lucretia was a noblewoman in ancient rome whose rape by sextus tarquinius (tarquin), an etruscan (italian civilization) king's son, was the cause of a rebellion that overthrew the roman monarchy and led to the transition of roman government from a kingdom to a republic.
•
since the renaissance, the suicide of lucretia has been an enduring subject for visual artists. most commonly, either the moment of the rape is shown or lucretia is shown alone at the moment of her suicide. in either situation, her clothing is loosened or absent.
•
the featured painting lucretia, by artemisia gentileschi, the female renaissance painter and now #metoo symbol, just sold for over $2 million in vienna recently.
•
as a teenager, gentileschi was raped by her art teacher, a man named agostino tassi. the case went to trial, and gentileschi underwent a humiliating physical examination and was tortured in order to prove the veracity of her claims before tassi was convicted and sentenced to exile. •
artemisia gentileschi's depictions of strong, powerful women are attracting a new wave of market and museum interest. in an era when female painters were not easily accepted by the artistic community or patrons, she was the first woman to become a member of the accademia di arte del disegno in florence and had international clientele.
she was independent, she was successful, she was in demand—and that was very unusual for that time, and has made her very much a symbol of modernity.
•
although her life story has sometimes over-shadowed her work, gentileschi didn’t let personal tragedy get in the way of her career. she became known for her dramatic, realistic depictions of women and sexual violence—work that seems incredibly timely in the age of #metoo. today, gentileschi’s embrace of this challenging subject matter has made her an important figure in symbolism for female struggle against tyranny.
•
#lucretia #artemisiagentileschi #feminism #metoo #famouspaintings #symbolism #neoculturation

text:
lekeisha sumner, ph.d., abpp is a licensed clinical psychologist with board-certification in clinical health psychology. she is the director of health 
psychology at cedars-sinai medical center and serves on the voluntary clinical faculty in the department of psychiatry at university of california, los angeles. 
she is a member of the california pain medicine center and was previously an associate professor of psychology in the california school of professional 
psychology at the los angeles campus of alliant international university, where she trained doctoral-level psychology students. dr. sumner's research and 
training, which examines the role of cultural, behavioral, and psychosocial factors in chronic illness and well-being, has been supported by the national institute of 
drug abuse and the national institute of mental health. dr. sumner has published widely on health and trauma among women and ethnic minorities. she was commissioned by the substance abuse and mental health services administration (#samhsa), center for substance abuse treatment to serve on the strategies for improving outcomes for peripartum women committee. she is a member of apa and has memberships in divisions 12, 39, and 35. she has served on the apa task force on trafficking of women and girls as well as the conference planning committee for the international summit on violence, abuse & trauma. she currently serves as the president of section iv, psychology of women, apa division 12 (clinical) and the committee on psychoanalysis in healthcare settings with division 39.

lekeisha sumner, ph.d., abpp is a licensed clinical psychologist with board-certification in clinical health psychology. she is the director of health 
psychology at cedars-sinai medical center and serves on the voluntary clinical faculty in the department of psychiatry at university of california, los angeles. 
she is a member of the california pain medicine center and was previously an associate professor of psychology in the california school of professional 
psychology at the los angeles campus of alliant international university, where she trained doctoral-level psychology students. dr. sumner's research and 
training, which examines the role of cultural, behavioral, and psychosocial factors in chronic illness and well-being, has been supported by the national institute of 
drug abuse and the national institute of mental health. dr. sumner has published widely on health and trauma among women and ethnic minorities. she was commissioned by the substance abuse and mental health services administration (#samhsa), center for substance abuse treatment to serve on the strategies for improving outcomes for peripartum women committee. she is a member of apa and has memberships in divisions 12, 39, and 35. she has served on the apa task force on trafficking of women and girls as well as the conference planning committee for the international summit on violence, abuse & trauma. she currently serves as the president of section iv, psychology of women, apa division 12 (clinical) and the committee on psychoanalysis in healthcare settings with division 39.
when you mix pink and black, you get #apaiswac. .
.
.
together we are unstoppable. .

text_retweet:
rp @jessyforthevoiceless 
graphic footage - cows can only produce milk after giving birth, so dairy farms have to constantly forcibly impregnate the cows. 
as a result, many baby calves are born. 
since male calves will never produce milk, they are of no use to a dairy farm. ▪ 
some farms let the calves live for a few months in order to slaughter them for veal.
an analysis shows that it can cost a farmer up to £30 per calf to sell it on for beef or veal, while 'early disposal' costs just £9.
▪ 
as seen, the workers shoot days-old calves in the head, then leave them to bleed in a mass grave. 
the worker doesn’t even make any special effort to shoot the calves in a way that will deliver a quick death. 
in addition, each calf only gets one bullet in order to save costs.
(this footage is from a dairy farm in florida).
but make no mistake, this happens all over the world.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
reposted from @lebanesevegans - just a normal and legal practice under the umbrella of “humane” slaughter. you can stop this by not buying dairy anymore. alternatives are everywhere.
.

text:
как многим известно 19 февраля скончался великий дизайнер и генеральный директор дома моды шанель - карл ларгельфилд

10 фактов о карле лагерфельде, которые вы могли не знать

1. карл отто лагерфельд родился 10 сентября 1933 года в гамбурге. впрочем, дизайнер оспаривал этот факт – он утверждал, что родился в 1938 году, а в одном из интервью заявил, что никто не знает его точный год рождения, но это и не 1933, и не 1938. как бы там ни было, он открыто признавался в том, что в детстве и юношестве мечтал стать аниматором. карл хотел рисовать мультфильмы, но также любил моду, и понимал, что фешн-индустрия может принести больший заработок. и оказался прав.

2. мать карла говорила ему, что у него уродливые руки. вероятно, это – одна из причин, по которым он всегда носил митенки.

3. еще одна знаковая часть образа кутюрье – волосы, собранные в хвостик – появилась в 1976 году. по словам дизайнера, однажды он устал от длинных кудрявых волос, но вместо стрижки предпочел носить аккуратный хвост.

4. обычной воде карл предпочитал pepsi или диетическую coca-cola. говорят, у дизайнера был специальный человек, который сопровождал его на вечеринках с бутылкой колы на подносе. а вот алкоголь лагерфельд не употреблял – говорил, что у него нет для этого времени.

5. карл жил на два дома. один был предназначен исключительно для работы и сна – в нем даже не было холодильника. помощники приносили ему еду, словно в отель. а в нескольких метрах от этого дома находится другой – в нем была столовая, кухня, и там карл принимал гостей.

6. но во всех домах дизайнера было множество книг – за свою жизнь лагерфельд собрал огромную библиотеку. при этом, он не любил так называемые coffee table books – тяжелые фото- и арт-книги большого формата, предназначенные для просмотра и хранения на кофейном столике. по мнению карла, книга должна быть компактной и удобной, чтобы ее можно было читать в кровати.

7. дизайнер нередко участвовал в коллаборациях, и многие из них были довольно необычными. к примеру, в 2011 году карл сотрудничал с известной маркой мороженого magnum, выступив креативным директором рекламной кампании. для этого кампейна карл придумал шоколадный гостиничный номер, в котором наход

5. карл жил на два дома. один был предназначен исключительно для работы и сна – в нем даже не было холодильника. помощники приносили ему еду, словно в отель. а в нескольких метрах от этого дома находится другой – в нем была столовая, кухня, и там карл принимал гостей.

6. но во всех домах дизайнера было множество книг – за свою жизнь лагерфельд собрал огромную библиотеку. при этом, он не любил так называемые coffee table books – тяжелые фото- и арт-книги большого формата, предназначенные для просмотра и хранения на кофейном столике. по мнению карла, книга должна быть компактной и удобной, чтобы ее можно было читать в кровати.

7. дизайнер нередко участвовал в коллаборациях, и многие из них были довольно необычными. к примеру, в 2011 году карл сотрудничал с известной маркой мороженого magnum, выступив креативным директором рекламной кампании. для этого кампейна карл придумал шоколадный гостиничный номер, в котором наход

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
recy taylor (née corbitt; december 31, 1919 – december 28, 2017):297 was an african-american woman from abbeville in henry county, alabama, u.s. she was born and raised in a sharecropping family in the jim crow era southern united states. taylor's refusal to remain silent about a brutal rape she suffered, perpetrated by white men, led to organizing in the african-american community on behalf of justice and civil rights.

on september 3, 1944, taylor was kidnapped while leaving church and gang-raped by six white men.[2]:xv-xvii despite the men's confessions to authorities, two grand juries subsequently declined to indict the men; no charges were ever brought against her assailants.

in 2011, the alabama legislature officially apologized on behalf of the state "for its failure to prosecute her attackers." taylor's rape, refusal to remain silent, and the subsequent court cases were among the early instances of nationwide protest and activism among the african-american community, and ended up providing an organizational spark in the civil rights movement ]:39

at the 2018 golden globe awards, while accepting the golden globe cecil b. demille award, oprah winfrey discussed and brought awareness to taylor's story. the congressional black caucus led democratic caucus members in wearing red "recy" pins while attending the 2018 state of the union, where taylor's granddaughter, mary joyce owens, was a guest.

link to trailer : https://youtu.be/rpudmdfequs
#recytaylor #documentaryfilm #blackhistorymonth2019 #syftkogtech #bijousfashions #metoo #blackgirlmagic #blackdads #movementculture

facts about a horrific crime
commercial child pornography is estimated to be a multi-billion dollar industry worldwide.
there are over 750,000 pedophiles online at any given time.
thousands of new images or videos are put on the internet every week.
hundreds of thousands of searches for child sexual abuse images are performed daily.
offenders may have collections of over a million child sexual abuse images.
an image of a 4-year-old girl in diapers has been shared an estimated 800,000 times.
most child sexual abuse image producers are known to the victims:
37 percent are family members.
36 percent are acquaintances.
over 30 percent of those convicted of possessing child pornography were living with minor children.
 almost 50 percent had access to minors at home, socially or as part of their jobs.

（續上）......andréa bescond之面對自己，尚在於將此經歷拍成作品傳揚後世。於電影壓軸一幕，成年版的odette卒之鼓起勇氣，打開那扇令人不安的門，與性侵現場裡昔日的小女孩odette對話；這個「超現實」安排，無疑是她的終極釋懷。的確，較諸父母、朋友和戀人，odette要真正突破自己的話，就必須直面自己的過去。這一幕裡，成人odette說自己一直將小女孩odette遺在洗手間，現在則要帶她走出枷鎖－－這一種釋懷，某程度是電影最最最催淚的部分。畢竟，小女孩odette豈非一直望眼欲穿，希望有人帶她走出深淵？而成年後的odette，亦一直希望有人幫助當年的自己，包括由她一手幫助性侵受害者......的確，這一幕存在雙重意義，andréa bescond牽著小女孩挺身而出，實也象徵她想牽著其他性侵受害者挺身而出－－她要拯救的，不止於戲裡的小女孩odette，而且還有世上千千萬萬個odette！片末交代歐洲的性侵數字，正正與此主題互相對照。
～
說了許多「以戲載道」的點讚位，不得不談的尚有上文一再提及的「現實」性質與「超現實」性質。
～
odette的人設無疑很「貼地」，例如愛好畫畫，又以舞蹈為目標，包括父母都想培育她當舞蹈員－－試問，這不是像極了許多小女孩的現況？的確，無論你我，任何人均可能是#metoo受害者。有人說，女孩版odette比成人版odette更加成功，理由是前者嬌嫩欲滴，後者不單被嚴重比下去，其風格也太過粗獷、太過狂野，以致不太討好觀眾云云......必須強調，如前所述，andréa bescond正正就是#metoo受害者，試問由她出演豈不順理成章？她的人物設定又哪來「不現實」？更重要是，不要以為只有外表討好的，才會淪為被性侵對象。君不見香港法庭新聞，許多弱者包括智障人士恰恰最易遭殃，而愈是弱勢者所受傷害亦恐愈大......事實上，odette的人生變得「墮落」，豈不進一步凸顯性侵對她的負面打擊？難道成人版odette繼續亭亭玉立、以至人格完美，這才叫「正常」、電影才「吸引」嗎？《說不出口的遊戲》正好道盡「現實」的一切不幸。
～
的確，不跳優雅的芭蕾舞，而跳著重情緒宣洩的現代舞及街舞，也是odette人設的一大成功之處；較諸平鋪直述純粹以對白交代，廣佈於電影不同階段的「超現實」舞蹈「突入」，便把odette當時心境展現得淋漓盡致，描寫感染力因而大大強化昇華。另外，她跟心理醫生等不時「突入」「超現實」的回憶片段，相關鏡頭運用不僅增添了電影玩味，odette於此「案發現場」和「假想空間」的「事後檢討」，同樣地，較諸刻板地透過旁白或回到醫生診所呈現，緊扣現場的張力與「貼地」感覺亦肯定強大得多。當然，凡此種種，更旨在鋪排最終壓軸「odette與odette對話」的重頭戲；倘無前面的「超現實」「前菜」，觀眾實不易接受及品嚐這幕「超現實」「主菜」。
～
筆者心想，如果電影結局再加一幕「超現實」情節，讓成人odette重返電影開初的第一幕，由她喝停gilbert帶走女孩odette進入洗手間－－如此的話，電影會否更加完美？然而，筆者很快就自我推翻了。因為，本片不在追求完美，而在告訴大家如何面對不完美，正如#metoo所著重的是舉報罪行，andréa bescond之所以拍攝本片也由於她已撫平昔日痛痕。雖然，假使odette父母事前有效關愛女兒，任何不幸誠有可能完全避免，電影也告誡現實中的父母要「多聽子女心底話」；不過，這裡的「多聽子女心底話」，亦更多在於為子女坦誠相向創造更佳條件，好使子女向父母道盡困擾、繼而讓父母解決子女困擾。透過本片，相信andréa bescond所希望傳遞的第一個願望，是鼓勵一眾性侵受害人挺身而出，即針對「事已至此」的人而言；第二個願望，才是鼓勵大家多關愛身邊人，毋使不幸悲劇一再發生、一再困住受害者。
～
無論如何，怎樣令「說不出口的遊戲」「說出口來」，包括由家長到社會怎樣營造「說得出口」的環境，無疑乃是#metoo精神的最佳體現。（劇透版二之二）
～
http://www.thinkhk.com/article/2019-02/22/33130.html
～
（影評全文，請瀏覽思考香港或facebook專頁）

stop_filter_tweet: 【說不出口的遊戲。影評】真人真事！有血有淚！來讓一切說得出口！ 李美 ～ （注意，以下完全劇透，有雷） ～ （續上） ... ... andréa bescond之面對自己，尚在於將此經歷拍成作品傳揚後世。於電影壓軸一幕，成年版的odette卒之鼓起勇氣，打開那扇令人不安的門，與性侵現場裡昔日的小女孩odette對話；這個「超現實」安排，無疑是她的終極釋懷。的確，較諸父母、朋友和戀人，odette要真正突破自己的話，就必須直面自己的過去。這一幕裡，成人odette說自己一直將小女孩odette遺在洗手間，現在則要帶她走出枷鎖－－這一種釋懷，某程度是電影最最最催淚的部分。畢竟，小女孩odette豈非一直望眼欲穿，希望有人帶她走出深淵？而成年後的odette，亦一直希望有人幫助當年的自己，包括由她一手幫助性侵受害者 ... ... 的確，這一幕存在雙重意義，andréa bescond牽著小女孩挺身而出，實也象徵她想牽著其他性侵受害者挺身而出－－她要拯救的，不止於戲裡的小女孩odette，而且還有世上千千萬萬個odette！片末交代歐洲的性侵數字，正正與此主題互相對照。 ～ 說了許多「以戲載道」的點讚位，不得不談的尚有上文一再提及的「現實」性質與「超現實」性質。 ～ odette的人設無疑很「貼地」，例如愛好畫畫，又以舞蹈為目標，包括父母都想培育她當舞蹈員－－試問，這不是像極了許多小女孩的現況？的確，無論你我，任何人均可能是 bescond正正就是etoo受害者，試問由她出演豈不順理成章？她的人物設定又哪來「不現實」？更重要是，不要以為只有外表討好的，才會淪為被性侵對象。君不見香港法庭新聞，許多弱者包括智障人士恰恰最易遭殃，而愈是弱勢者所受傷害亦恐愈大 ... ... 事實上，odette的人生變得「墮落」，豈不進一步凸顯性侵對她的負面打擊？難道成人版odette繼續亭亭玉立、以至人格完美，這才叫「正常」、電影才「吸引」嗎？《說不出口的遊戲》正好道盡「現實」的一切不幸。 ～ 的確，不跳優雅的芭蕾舞，而跳著重情緒宣洩的現代舞及街舞，也是odette人設的一大成功之處；較諸平鋪直述純粹以對白交代，廣佈於電影不同階段的「超現實」舞蹈「突入」，便把odette當時心境展現得淋漓盡致，描寫感染力因而大大強化昇華。另外，她跟心理醫生等不時「突入」「超現實」的回憶片段，相關鏡頭運用不僅增添了電影玩味，odette於此「案發現場」和「假想空間」的「事後檢討」，同樣地，較諸刻板地透過旁白或回到醫生診所呈現，緊扣現場的張力與「貼地」感覺亦肯定強大得多。當然，凡此種種，更旨在鋪排最終壓軸「odette與odette對話」的重頭戲；倘無前面的「超現實」「前菜」，觀眾實不易接受及品嚐這幕「超現實」「主菜」。 ～ 筆者心想，如果電影結局再加一幕「超現實」情節，讓成人odette重返電影開初的第一幕，由她喝停gilbe帶走女孩odette進入洗手間－－如此的話，電影會否更加完美？然而，筆者很快就自我推翻了。因為，本片不在追求完美，而在告訴大家如何面對不完美，正如 bescond之所以拍攝本片也由於她已撫平昔日痛痕。雖然，假使odette父母事前有效關愛女兒，任何不幸誠有可能完全避免，電影也告誡現實中的父母要「多聽子女心底話」；不過，這裡的「多聽子女心底話」，亦更多在於為子女坦誠相向創造更佳條件，好使子女向父母道盡困擾、繼而讓父母解決子女困擾。透過本片，相信andréa bescond所希望傳遞的第一個願望，是鼓勵一眾性侵受害人挺身而出，即針對「事已至此」的人而言；第二個願望，才是鼓勵大家多關愛身邊人，毋使不幸悲劇一再發生、一再困住受害者。 ～ 無論如何，怎樣令「說不出口的遊戲」「說出口來」，包括由家長到社會怎樣營造「說得出口」的環境，無疑乃是etoo精神的最佳體現。（劇透版二之二） ～ ～ （影評全文，請瀏覽思考香港或facebook專頁） ～ 美 影 不出口的遊戲 能說的遊戲 瘙癢 ittletickles hetickling hedanceofwrath ndréabescond yrillemairesse arolefranck ricmétayer etoo ovie

text:
zhenya also acted on 'imitation of hanyu' even while acting fs.
even if it does not match the tango's rhythm at all, zenya did the action of "action seeking crowd enthusiasm".
she imitated the behavior of hanyu's "let's go crazy", but the audience was puzzled because it did not fit the rhythm.
symptoms of "hanyu imitation disease" by zenya have worsened in recent years.
when she was at teameteri, zhenya did not do such a performance. as the opportunity to go to the tcc grows, she rapidly worsens "hanyu imitation disease."
if i were hanyu, i do not like such an eerie fake.

text:
“the ‘r’ word” is the latest piece from jamie (@jamieandboo_art). as with all of jamie’s work, “the ‘r’ word” tackles a difficult and, for some, an uncomfortable subject matter. 
but for those that we’ve met in the four months we’ve been on this journey, jamie’s work has provided comfort and a sense of hope for people who’ve not only experienced sexual violence; but also those that have suffered from depression and mental health issues and continue to do so. 
it’s been a moving and humbling experience to see the impact that jamie’s work is already having. and we’ll continue to push boundaries, challenge conventions and speak uncomfortable truths in our quest to start a conversation that brings about actual change.

the work we’re doing with specific charities will also form part of that quest for change. a change in behaviour and a change in attitude towards those that can feel isolated and excluded because of what they’ve faced and continue to face on a daily basis.

it just leaves us to say a huge thank you to everyone that has supported us thus far and please don’t be afraid to show your support in the future.

with genuine love and respect 
bam & jamie

it just leaves us to say a huge thank you to everyone that has supported us thus far and please don’t be afraid to show your support in the future.

with genuine love and respect 
bam & jamie

“don’t you get it, even if ‘innocent until proven guilty,’ you’re encouraging the disgusting, vile behaviour they’ve been accused of, and also, encouraging others to do so by demonstrating that they can get away with it without any serious repercussions.”

“i am an opinionated woman, and will remain so – you can call it a publicity stunt or whatever you want,” she said.

text:
top #metoo advocate’s son accused of assault
#
web desk: an organization time’s up was formed last year to deal with sexual harassment and assault in the workplace, is now coping with a crisis within its own ranks. according to bloomberg report, chief executive officer lisa borders, who announced she was stepping down earlier this week, left the organization because her son was accused of sexual misconduct, time’s up disclosed late thursday. “lisa borders informed members of time’s up leadership that sexual assault allegations had been made against her son in a private forum,” the group said in an emailed statement. “within 24 hours, lisa made the decision to resign as president and ceo of time’s up and we agreed that it was the right decision for all parties involved. all of our actions were fully guided by our support for survivors.” time’s up issued the statement after the los angeles times reported that borders’s son, garry “dijon” bowden jr., was accused of violating a woman while giving her a massage. a lawyer for bowden disputed the woman’s account, saying there was no inappropriate or nonconsensual touching, according to the times. when borders announced her resignation earlier this week, she said it was to address “family concerns that require my singular…

text:
singer r. kelly is scheduled to appear in court this morning for a bail hearing after his arrest on charges of sexual abuse spanning from 1998 to 2010.

cook county state's attorney kim foxx announced yesterday that the r&b musician, whose full name is robert kelly, was indicted on 10 counts of aggravated criminal sexual abuse -- a class two felony -- involving four alleged victims.

the indictment accuses kelly of sexual acts with three children older than 13 but younger than 17. there is no age range listed for one of the alleged victims. the charges say kelly used force or the threat of force.

to learn more visit legalactionnews.com

text:
it’s hard to describe how it feels watch r. kelly’s downfall unfold. the only word i can think of is relief. it’s just such a deep relief to see that people are finally believing the truth about this man. 
i remember being 13 and watching the mtv news report about him marrying aaliyah when she was only 15 years old and i remember a decade later hearing about him urinating on a 14 year old. the truth was always there to see but was normalized and excused because he made good music. 
the past several years with the #metoo movement, #timesup, and the number of men and women who have come forward with their experiences have made me realize how much i had normalized the predatory behavior of men. how i have been conditioned to accept such behavior to the point where i considered it an unpleasant part of life to try to avoid instead of something to stand up against. 
r. kelly is not an anomaly, he’s just rich. there are many predatory men out there who engage in similar behavior on a much smaller scale. i hope that all of their victims find justice. 
thank you to #muterkelly founders kenyette tisha barnes and oronike odeleye and to #metoo founder tarana burke for all of their terribly difficult work. 
#blackgirlslivesmatter #protectblackwomen #protectblackgirls #muterkelly

text:
🎞história // isa grinspum ferraz é a socióloga e cinesta que dirigiu, em 2012, o documentário sobre a vida do seu tio, carlos marighella. o revolucionário e autor do manual do guerrilheiro urbano, foi assassinado pela polícia em 1969, na ditadura militar. com narração de lázaro ramos, o filme conta a história de marighella por meio de memórias afetivas e depoimentos de pessoas próximas a ele, como a viúva clara charf. .
.
vale lembrar que, neste ano, o ator wagner moura estreia como diretor com um filme que também conta a vida do revolucionário. em berlim, moura posou para fotos segurando uma placa de rua com o nome de marielle franco, assassinada em março do ano passado, num ainda crime sem punição. para ver hoje.

text:
本日は石川幸子をcelebrateさせていただきます。父が日本人、母がドイツ人で、スペインのバルセロナで育ちました。フェミニストであり、仕事はフィクション作家と翻訳者。今は東京に住んでいます。

女性をもっと雇用し、管理職に就かせるべきです。実際に女性が意思決定を行える立場に立てなければ何も変わりません。また、「＃metoo⁠ ⁠」運動が世界に広がる今、日本のエンターテインメント業界も対策をとるべきです。

決してあきらめたり、人任せにしたりしないでください。年齢やジェンダー、性的指向／アイデンティティー、政治に対する考え方などに関わらず、一人ひとりが女性の権利のために戦うべきです。行動を起こさない人は、女性を取り巻く問題の一部となってしまいます。#アドバイス 
today we celebrate sachiko ishikawa, half-japanese and half-german but was raised in barcelona, spain. she is a feminist, a fiction writer and a translator. sachiko currently lives in tokyo. 
hire women, and give them positions of power. we won’t change anything until the system has actual female representation. also, the entertainment industry needs to update itself in the #metoo⁠ ⁠era. 
don’t shrug and hope others will fight for your rights. regardless of your age, gender, sexual orientation/identity, political views, etc. this is still your fight. and if you’re not a part of the solution, you’re part of the problem. 
#profilenumber328
#celebratingwomeninjapan
