text:
there’s something i’ve realize about sexual assault that no one likes to admit. one night at work, i was grabbed from behind by a stranger, strangled and sexually assaulted. within four hours he was arrested (there’s also a lot to say about vengeance being best served cold; whomever said that has never enjoyed a nice, pipping-hot plate of fresh vengeance). during the court process, he was found guilty and sentenced to 3 years. i’ll never forget what a woman on the prosecution said to me, “people will tell you, you need to forgive him. the secret is; you don’t have to”. it was at that moment i understood the power of unforgiveness. forgiving him was expected of me, and in that, there was oppression. forgiveness can be oppressive for the victim. when i decided not to, it was liberating and in that i found a bit of power back that he had taken from me. 
so here’s to secret for other sexual assault victims; you don’t have to forgive if you don’t want to. the choice belongs to you, no one else. he took from me a lot. he won’t take that. #metoo #sexualassault #survivor #unforgiveness #forgiveness #oppressiveness #journaling #journal

text:
on nait, on vit, on meurt.

je suis charlie, je suis citoyen du monde, je suis un punk à chien, je suis un couple de stars sur un voilier, je suis bénévole dans une ong, je suis un marchand d'olives en grèce, je suis un soldat en afghanistan, je suis un champ de lavandes dans la drôme, je suis un réveil cassé, je suis l'amour après minuit, je suis une bouteille de vin ouverte et vidée sur une terrasse, je suis un aigle qui disparaît dans le brouillard, je suis une île vierge remplie de serpents, de rats et de koalas, je suis un touriste allemand sur la grande muraille de chine, je suis une photographie d'amour oubliée dans un tiroir, je suis un labrador qui court dans le jardin d'une veuve, je suis un chat errant dans la capitale, je suis un scorpion sous le sable, je suis une publicité exposée à times square, je suis un roman de camus, je suis un homard plongé vivant dans une casserole d'eau bouillante, je suis la canicule en andalousie, je suis un drone qui tire sur des irakiens, je suis une femme de ménage dans un hôtel quatre étoiles, je suis une partie de pétanque dans le sud, je suis une ruche décimée par monsanto, je suis une enfant dans le carrosse d'un manège, je suis un cheval qui galope dans les plaines de la mongolie, je suis un médicament à la fin du repas, je suis une actrice à quatre pattes, je suis un réalisateur à cannes, je suis une cassette rembobinée, je suis une route enneigée, je suis un château de cartes, je suis un tour de magie, je suis un enfant qui fugue, je suis une émission de télévision, je suis un maquillage raté, je suis une tentative de viol, je suis un loup blessé, je suis un corps dans un cimetière, je suis une bible brûlée, je suis un tube de l'été, je suis un écran solaire qui se dissout dans l'océan, je suis une femme réduite à son tour de poitrine, je suis le bruit insupportable d'un marteau piqueur à huit heures du matin, je suis un métro qui pue la sueur, je suis un clochard près du canal saint-martin, je suis #metoo, je suis un journal froissé, je suis une grève de la ratp ; je suis comme tout le monde mais je veux être différent.

on nait, on vit, on meurt et je suis comme tout le monde car je veux être différent.

text_retweet:
makes me have to rethink the cheese i am eating a few times a month. beef (and mammalian and bird meat) has been off the menu for years. ///// rp @jessyforthevoiceless 
graphic footage - cows can only produce milk after giving birth, so dairy farms have to constantly forcibly impregnate the cows. 
as a result, many baby calves are born. 
since male calves will never produce milk, they are of no use to a dairy farm. ▪ 
some farms let the calves live for a few months in order to slaughter them for veal.
an analysis shows that it can cost a farmer up to £30 per calf to sell it on for beef or veal, while 'early disposal' costs just £9.
▪ 
as seen, the workers shoot days-old calves in the head, then leave them to bleed in a mass grave. 
the worker doesn’t even make any special effort to shoot the calves in a way that will deliver a quick death. 
in addition, each calf only gets one bullet in order to save costs.
(this footage is from a dairy farm in florida).
but make no mistake, this happens all over the world.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
reposted from @lebanesevegans - just a normal and legal practice under the umbrella of “humane” slaughter. you can stop this by not buying dairy anymore. alternatives are everywhere.
.

text:
share your story. 
quite simply, hearing the stories of other women who have walked this path is the number one thing that has lifted my spirits and got me going again.  thank you.

hearing from the women who have come through it all. survived. maybe a little battle weary, but radiant none the less. these are the stories that show us all we can do it. we can choose to leave if the situation at home is causing harm. 
thank you to everyone who has reached out this week with words of encouragement and love and support. 
now i really understand why sharing your story is important. even if it’s a little socially inappropriate to be truthful and brazen and unapologetic about how your journey played out, to someone somewhere it might be the key to helping them see clearly their own journey and the unthinkable path of choosing differently. 
share your story. not for yourself, but for every woman out there who needs to know she’s not alone. ❤️

#repost from @metooethiopia (@repost_media_app)
taytu betul was an empress of ethiopia. similar to the 65 percent of ethiopian women, taytu encountered genital mutilation before she was three months old. because of the damage caused by genital mutilation, taytu was unable to give birth. fortunately, the humiliation she faced didn’t become an obstacle for taytu. infact, taytu played a major role influencing her husband to be against any negotiations that would cause colonization. when negotiations wasn’t becoming effective, taytu and her husband rode their army together to fight. because of her guidance, the ethiopian army had victory at adwa. inaddition, the addis ababa we love and know today was discovered by taytu. not believing in cultural perceptions, taytu took full control when her husband fell ill. although taytu was fortune enough to avoid death caused by genital mutilation,  65 percent of ethiopian women still encounter genital mutilation. without any knowledge about female’s body, the people who perform genital mutilation cause death and kill women’s purpose. eventhough genital mutilation is illegal in ethiopia, the problem is still prevalent. sign the petition to fight genital mutilation and injustice women face for just being a human. sign the petition to prove assault is a crime, not a culture.

text:
child labour refers to the exploitation of children through any form of work that deprives children of their childhood, interferes with their ability to attend regular school, and is mentally, physically, socially or morally harmful.
the main reason for child labour is poverty. most of the country's population suffers from poverty. due to poverty, parents cannot afford the studies of their children and make them earn their wages from a tender age. in fact, they are well aware of the grief of losing their loved ones to poverty many times.
.

the time's up movement against sexual harassment, founded a year ago, has made tangible progress in the world of showbiz and beyond -- by fostering solidarity and encouraging women to speak out -- but the road ahead is indeed long.

on january 1, 2018, more than 300 top women in hollywood unveiled a manifesto for change, with the goal of "shifting our society's perception and treatment of women. " "for too long, women have not been heard or believed if they dare speak the truth to the power of those men," winfrey said to a standing ovation and even some tears in the audience. "so i want all the girls watching here now to know that a new day is on the horizon." - oprah winfrey

the #metoo movement which spurred the #nomore campaign in nigeria has freed up women to speak up.

woomen are more willing to speak out, sharing their stories because they know it can help others.

text:
trenell:
trenell eaton, is a woman of god first and a superhero mother to her son.  born and partially raised in the district of columbia, trenell developed a resilience to her childhood traumas. despite her shortcomings, she was able to overcome the adversity of having survived multiple episodes of homelessness, abuse, and poverty.  instead of falling victim to statistical outcomes she decided that she would use her plights to build a platform for herself and women and girls just like her across the world.

trenell earned a bachelor's degree in sociology from morgan state university and is completing her masters of jurisprudence in child law and policy at loyola university of chicago school of law.  currently she manages special education schools for the dc public schools and serves as an advocate for children in her community.  in addition, trenell is the founder of the non-profit organization i am beautiful because, a woman’s awareness organization that supports women and girls who have been victims of child sexual abuse.  this is seed that was planted from her own person experience with child sexual abuse. "i needed a hero so, i became one" 
#iambeautifulbecause #metoo #womenempoweringwomen #womenempoweringgirls #nonprofit

text:
джордж мендоса, целующий медсестру на знаменитой фотографии 1945-го года альфреда эйзенштадта «поцелуй на таймс-сквер» (также известной как «день победы на таймс-сквер») умер в сша в возрасте 95 лет за два дня до своего дня рождения. r.i.p. 
медсестра, которую он целовал, ушла из жизни три года назад. 🔥 традиционно, по-американски был поставлен памятник повторяющий эту сцену, на котором несколько дней назад фемен-активистки краской написали «ми ту», обмитушили... из масс-медиа: "нечего так убиваться из-за осквернения памятника. фото не было романтичным. моряк был пьяным, поцелуй - насильным". washington post. 👌 мудаки! скоро их начнут бить? 🤔 #metoo #идиот #идиоты #война #победа #история #фото #женщина #женщины #девушка #моряк #ньюйорк

a #nashville lawsuit claims a teenage sex trafficking #survivor was the victim of "quests for profits" by facebook and a hotel chain.

the then-15-year-old girl's mother sued facebook, rodeway inn and related companies this week.

the lawsuit says facebook didn't verify a 35-year-old man's identity, prevent communication with minors or intervene before he persuaded the teen to leave home via private facebook messaging.
it says a nashville rodeway inn ignored visible signs of physical and #sexualabuse.

to learn more visit legalactionnews.com

text:
i’m currently visiting framily in dc. i always feel split in two here: there’s the part of me that’s so excited to be invited into these people’s beautiful lives and then the part of me that feels like an intruder, that i don’t belong. i have to constantly remind myself that the voice telling me i don’t belong is an old narrative from a traumatic childhood. the truth is that i do belong, just as i am. i’m learning to breathe that in and allow it to transform stale beliefs into grounded loving truths. the life i live now is so very different from my past. i invite my affect to match my present circumstances, not my past. how are you surrounding yourself with love and belonging today? how are you allowing them to change outdated beliefs about yourself?
.
.
.
#recovery #metoo #love #belonging #peace #truth #selfcare #selfhelp #help #happiness #fulfillment #invitations

text:
"savage news" by jessica yellin.
3.5 stars ⭐⭐⭐ 1/2

well... it is rather light read, not too exciting but neither boring. it kind of reflects the world we are leaving in, where woman are not treated equally and where there is sexism and sexual assault at work of place.

i didn't like the main character natalie too much. i liked the idea of the story and the theme of journalism and reporting for the tv station. 
but there wasn't anything too mysterious or thrilling or suspenseful in this novel.

about:
be noisy. natalie savage grew up hearing these words from her beloved father, who admired walter cronkite so much he named the family dog after him. natalie--who spent her twenties missing out on life's benchmarks--finally sees her efforts pay off when she's assigned to cover the white house for her network, atn. the problem? the position is only temporary, a test to see if she has what it takes. she has always relied on her grit, her principles and her news sense to gain success. but now her competition is a twenty-six-year-old spoiled frat boy who got his big television break by eating raw animal parts on a reality show.of course, he's winning.natalie, along with her scrappy production team, has to navigate ratings wars, workplace sexual harassment and an international political crisis in order to prove herself. but the closer she gets to achieving her dream job, the more she wonders if it is worth all the compromise.timely, funny and smart, this juicy debut is the perfect tonic for readers contending with today's politics and the #metoo movement.

text:
barthélemy toguo's works are inclusive, beautiful and awakening. making the residents participate in his works that deal with migration and its effects, he makes the entire process highly collaborative. in late 2018, he gave a platform to children to let out their emotions which flowed with the floods that were the worst to hit kerala in ten years. he invited them to write about how the floods affected them and their families, on previously stamped handmade water color postcards. these postcards, displayed for all to read are bound to trigger empathy within viewers. he further printed woodcuts made from huge stamps that were sculpted from wood, with the help of his chainsaw. banners and slogans that have dominated social media the past year were carved on these stamps, of which prints were taken later and displayed for all to read. the issues from #metoo, to land struggles were portrayed, and it highlighted how social media, in many ways, bears the torch to lead protests. toguo's works strike a chord with a viewer's sense of inclusivity and progression, helping all of us to understand where we stand and what can be or could be, as we consider the current and past circumstances. 
#kochibiennale#kochimuzirisbiennale#kmb2018#kmb2019#kochi#artistsoninstagram#arteverywhere#thatundocumentedart#throwback#artist#sculpture#sculptor#printmaking#stamps#postcards#socialissues#collaborative#instadaily

.

text:
just in time for the 91st academy awards on sunday: a special oscars edition of @femtastic_podcast! 🍿
🌟"the oscars edition - inclusion riders, workplace diversity, and we guess movies" 🌟
🍿
katie speaks to law partner in civil rights and employment, @kalpanakotagal, about one of the most googled terms following last year's oscars: inclusion rider.
🍿
kalpana - one of the co-authors of the inclusion rider - discusses what an inclusion rider is, how it works to increase diversity in hollywood productions (on-screen and off), and why it comes up in the discussion of #metoo. they also discuss ways that anyone (including you!) can make a difference to promote diversity in their workplaces, even when they don't have the leverage of a hollywood a-lister or c-suite exec. 🍿 
listen to the podcast at the link in bio, spotify, itunes, or on pretty much any podcast player. 🍿

text:
🔊🔛and the oscar goes to.....who does not love watching the oscars, @theacademy the glitz, the glamour. watching the actors, the directors, the make-up artists, cinematography, costume designers, screenwriters, etc., of the best films of the past year and many using the platform to make political or social comments in their acceptance speech. what @leonardodicaprio said on winning #bestactor for #therevenant in 2016 ‘let us not take this planet for granted.’ over the past few years we have had #timesup #metoo #oscarssowhite #equalpay #bechdeltest #inclusionrider #genderequality campaigns. the academy and the #movieindustry has tried to address these issues but there is still some way to go as well as getting representation on both sides of the camera. 
in this interview adam mckay, ( @ghostpanther2018) oscar winner for best writing adapted screenplay for #thebigshot  is considering his next movie project to be about the greatest threat to our planet, #climatechange #globalwarming
talking at the end of this interview with francine stock (@stockfrancine ) on #thefilmprogramme @bbcsounds @bbcradio4 adam mckay talks about his next movie project potentially collaborating with @yeswillferrell

very proud to be sharing this work created in collaboration with @micaela_mamede for her awe inspiring choreography performance at gibney dance, this is #maria2018. produced and performed by an ensemble of non-us immigrant women and allies, maria tells the all too common story of violence and silence immigrant women face. this whole project was made possible by micaela and her unwavering visual mission to share her own voice. she's since gained the support of the #healmetoo festival, a grassroots foundation working to heal victims of sexual violence by funding creative, therapeutic outlets for victims. please join us at the first ever nyc heal me too festival march 27-april 19, 2019. to learn more about their work, please follow @micaela_mamede and @healmetoofest and visit www.healmetoofest.com #metoo #womenshistorymonth #intimatepartnerviolence #healing - makeup by @batamakeup and cast: #danutapetrow-sek #emilyteller #hayetmoutfi, #krishnawashburn #malaikacambridge #maluavalos #mariasek #micaelamamede and #pearlbhatnagar - thank you ladies. xo

text:
two days until explore more summit 2019 begins. if you've been thinking about joining us, now is the time.
.
what is explore more summit?
.
take an in-person conference with all those rich discussions and big ideas from rad people doing important work in the world and then bring it online.
.
we've got 27 conversations unfolding over 10 days with 2-3 one-hour talks per day. it's totally free to attend. you watch as much or as little as you'd like, from the comfort of your own home (or sneaking it at work, like i used to do with online conferences).
.
plus, each day of the conference you get a free workbook with dozens of journal prompts, activities, and questions to help you bring the big ideas into your own life in an ultra-personal way.
.
the theme this year is finding power in personal and collective pleasure. there are talks on pleasure, erotic breathwork, healing, trauma, burnout, stress, disability justice, boundaries, anger, chronic illness, diet culture, body love, parenting, and soooo much more.
.
if you'd like to join us, you can register at exploremoresummit.com.
.
if you'd like to check out the amazing line-up and session titles, that's at exploremoresummit.com/summit-schedule
.
plus, we have a huge facebook group full of folks eager to explore their more alongside you! we talk about feelings, stuck places, hopes, dreams, ask questions, even interact with some of the speakers.
.
i am so excited and so nervous and holy smokes! two days before it starts! .
i'll see you there.
.

text:
this is a heavily discussed topic. i’ve read so many thoughts on abortion, i’ve boiled mine down to this. ➡️bringing a new life into this world if the mother doesn’t want it, i think is wrong. every child deserves to be truly loved and wanted.
➡️pregnancy is a huge undertaking and no woman should be forced into this. it is her body to decide what to do with.
➡️a woman does not have to find the choice of abortion difficult. sometimes she will know immediately this is the right choice for her.
➡️some women do not fall pregnant through choice. victims of rape and abuse need the choice of abortion.
➡️needing an abortion does not automatically mean a woman has not planned her contraception. contraception can on occasion not work.

what are your thoughts?

text:
eve, i see you (self portrait); chicago, il, 2019. 📷 #drb_mywildest 
women’s access to knowledge has been limited or blocked around the world for too long. i am grateful i was able to learn, supported by my family to mentally explore what it means to be human/e. the apple contains sacred geometry, a pentagram and pentagon of perfect proportions: five elliptical tiny spaceships for five seeds to sprout and bloom. the number 5 is, in numerology and yantra, associated with growth, change, movement, freedom, dance, transformation. i see you, eve, grabbing that apple and saying no to lack of self-knowledge and awareness in the name of subservience. i see you, eve, listening to the great serpent of your kundalini rising to teach you the sacred geometry of your body and soul, the alchemy of your orgasms. i see you women, risking your lives to learn and love. i love you.

text:
hey #toronto!! // pretty psyched to get this one into the calendar. kitchen table conversations with an incredible group of folx on march 8 at apartment 200. all women and feminized folx are welcome to attend. celebrate international women’s day with us. more details and how to get your complimentary ticket in the link @minibarcanada’s profile (or https://iwd2019toronto.eventbrite.ca) .
.
about kitchen table conversations, “"kitchen table conversations can ignite action, create community, solve problems, reduce barriers and start revolutions. women and feminized people have used kitchen table conversations to reclaim their narratives and empower one another, today we are going to do the same. we are bringing together diverse groups of women and non-binary people in the food, beverage and hospitality industry to collaborate, knowledge exchange, network and build bridges to creating real change." - viktoria belle, founder, dandelion initiative .
.

text:
depuis quelques années, cette figure féminine venue du moyen age, qui symbolise la femme subversive, séduit à la fois le théâtre, le cinéma et l’édition.
a l’heure de #metoo et de la troisième vague féministe, le phénomène, que l’on voyait monter depuis plusieurs années, s’est cristallisé avec la sortie du livre de mona chollet, sorcières. la puissance invaincue des femmes.

a l’heure de #metoo et de la troisième vague féministe, le phénomène, que l’on voyait monter depuis plusieurs années, s’est cristallisé avec la sortie du livre de #monachollet, #sorcières. la puissance invaincue des femmes (zones, 2018). c’est le succès d’édition le plus inattendu de cet hiver 2018-2019 : déjà plus de 75 000 exemplaires vendus, un chiffre sans aucune mesure avec les précédents ­livres de l’auteure publiés aux éditions ­zones. on s’offre l’ouvrage de mona chollet entre amies, comme un viatique sur la voie d’une libération qui, pour les femmes, est loin d’être terminée.

text_retweet:
#repost @lizzyrussinko
・・・
consent culture begins in childhood.
======================
“i’m going to pick you up now,” i said to my newborn son softly, nestling my hands around the muslin blanket that swaddled his tiny body. i picked him up and cradled him close to my chest, nuzzling my nose and lips against the top of his head, breathing in his sweet newborn smell. he couldn’t verbalize “yes” or “no” yet, but communicating this action was still important. to me, to him – to all of us. it is in these moments that we lay the groundwork for consent culture.
.
over the last couple of years #metoo has opened up an active global dialogue that once felt somewhat relegated to a passionate minority (and a whispering majority). we are collectively exploring ways of disrupting patriarchal culture that perpetuates sexual violence, and one of the most powerful things we can do is raise humans that have a clear understanding of consent.
.
objectification is at the root of sexual violence; it is part of what allows one person to act upon another without consent. when we communicate bodily respect to even the tiniest human, we are honoring and respecting them as a subject, as opposed to an object. we are teaching our children that they are an active participant in their human experience, and that all human beings are subjects with bodily agency. this is just the beginning of instilling our children with respect for others.
.
there are so many ways that we can incorporate an understanding of consent into our children’s lives. don’t force them to hug or kiss relatives. teach them the proper names for their genitalia. communicate what you are doing to a child during care giving activities like bath time and diaper changes. encourage them to ask permission before hugging or kissing playmates. explain that “no means no” and respect those boundaries when playing physical games like tickling and roughhousing. be role model for empathy toward others in your daily interactions.
.
consent culture begins in childhood.

#consentculture #metoo #rieparenting #handletteringmisfit #raisinginclusivekids #respectfulparenting #handmadefont #handlettered #thisunscriptedlife

text:
do you feel like your life isn’t your own?

perhaps you’ve reached a point in your life where you are tired of not living your life as you have dreamed, or you put others priorities first.

or you are tired of “waiting until tomorrow” to make changes because tomorrow never happens and you are ready to do what is needed so your life can be your own.

wouldn’t it be great to take care of you?  what a great gift to yourself 💜. to sign up for your complimentary call, click on link in bio ▶️ @denisestyer and let’s discuss how you can give yourself the gift you deserve! 💕💕

text:
the #narcissist who abused me claims to be #muslim, but narcissists’ tendency to hide behind & bastardise #religion is absolutely not exclusive to muslims & please no muslim-bashing.
.
.
.
this so-called muslim has had sex with men, uses cocaine, used to sell & use crack, has sex with prostitutes, drinks alcohol & mostly seems unfussed about whether his food is halal or not.  still, he uses his “faith” (not that it sounds like he’s even serious about his faith given his lifestyle) to condone his exploitative, misogynistic conduct towards women.  specifically towards non-muslim women. (i’m catholic)
.
.
the narc feels he has the god-given right to subject non-muslim to sexual exploitation & psychological violence purely because they’re not muslim, & therefore — in his warped mind— are “whores” & “asking for it.” after lying to me about the relationship status, exploiting me & eventually admitting his intention to abandon his unborn child, the narc said it was all my fault.  that because i’d proven willing to have sex with him without being married, and because i have my own home, i must’ve “known what this was” & realised that he was lying when he said we were dating.  eh? 
the narc seems to believe #allah condones his grotesque & calculatedly exploitative behaviour.
.
.
.
like many narcs, this one had a serious case of #madonnawhorecomplex.  he divides women into 2 categories: non-muslim women, there to be used like prostitutes then thrown away.  muslim women (with some other caveats, such as them having to be younger than him & uneducated) - for marriage & kids (but still abused, just in different ways). .
.
.when the narc was called out on this he was shockingly upfront about it, claiming that sexually exploiting non-muslim women is a better alternative than using prostitutes. 😢😢😱
he added; “you’ve got no right to have my baby. it’s unnatural.”
why lie though? why not just find a woman who’s willing to engage in a relationship where they’re used like a sperm receptacle while the narc scavenges around for a suitable muslim victim?  the narc’s response: “a woman like that might have health issues. i’d be worried about catching something”
continues in comments

text: i am bothered by the hero worship surrounding this man. it is time we stop allowing horrible attitudes and  behaviors just because they come from talented men. it is in fact possible to be both a creative genius and a bad person. karl lagerfeld hated the #metoo movement. he believed that any woman who wanted agency over her own body belonged in the nunnery, and only women who were willing to be man handled had the right to work in fashion. any person who doesn’t believe that every human being should have the right to make decisions about how and when their bodies can be touched, will always perpetuate rape culture whether they are actually perpetrating sexual assaults or not. i spend my free time working with an agency who helps victims of sexual violence, so before you tell me i’m too sensitive about our culture and how it perpetuates violence against many, especially women, ask yourself if your beliefs and actions do anything to help the people in your life who have been affected by this issue. trust me, we all know multiple people who have been affected by sexual violence, so why don’t we change our attitudes to make this country better and stronger for all. also, if you are disgusted by r. kelly and bill cosby, but are still supporters of karl lagerfeld and roman polanski, maybe there are some other biases that you need to closely analyze within your own heart.🤷🏼‍♀️ #sorrynotsorry #downwiththepatriarchy

text:
#nmn1 #nmnisreal #ladiesofthenmn #menofthenmn #courtesyof @fox5dc chicago (ap) - r. kelly was ordered jailed on $1 million bond saturday at his first court hearing since the r&b star was charged with sexually abusing four people, including three minors, in a case that seemed likely to produce another #metoo trial involving a celebrity.
the 52-year-old grammy winner turned himself in late friday and spent a night in jail before being taken to the courthouse. he stood with his hands behind his back and said to the judge, "how are you?"
kelly's attorney, steve greenberg, said his client is not a flight risk and told the judge, "contrary to the song, mr. kelly doesn't like to fly." the bond requires kelly to post $100,000 to be released.

cook county judge john fitzgerald lyke jr. called the allegations "disturbing." he said the bail amount equals $250,000 for each of the four people kelly is charged with abusing. the singer-songwriter looked down at the floor as judge spoke.
a prosecutor told the judge that kelly met one of the four accusers at his 2008 trial on child pornography charges. the two met when he gave her an autograph, and the abuse occurred between 2009 and 2010. the accuser gave law enforcement a shirt that had kelly's dna on it, the prosecutor said.
he has been trailed for decades by allegations that he violated underage girls and women and held some as virtual slaves. he was charged with 10 counts of aggravated sexual abuse. authorities said the abuse dated back as far as 1998 and spanned more than a decade.
kelly, who was acquitted of child pornography charges in 2008, has consistently denied any sexual misconduct. greenberg told reporters following the singer's arrest that one of the charges he faces appears to be tied to a decade-old child pornography case.
"double jeopardy should bar that case," greenberg said. "he won that case."
greenberg said prosecutors rushed to judgment friday in charging kelly. he called the singer "an innocent man." "mr. kelly is strong," greenberg added. "he's got a lot of support, and he's going to be vindicated on all these charges."

text:
امثال این فرد زیاد هستند خیلی زیاد خیلی زیاد #جواب این چی می خوای بدید اینم عوامل #موساد . دستنشانده #غرب از شیطان بزرگ #جینگیلی_آمریکا  خط گرفته . جواب اینو چی میدید 
آقای شیخ پرزیدنت دکتر حجت السلام #روحانی آقای نابغه اقتصاد #نوبخت و #دلواپسان_در_اینده_سیاسی_ایران_جایی_ندارند  شما که همه را دشمن خودتان می دانید جواب بدید چی دارید بگید و در آخر اون بالا البته نه زیاد بالا #آقا وی جواب دارید باز هم #دژمن 
جناب #جعفرزاده که هر جا باد بیاد شما هم باهاش میایی جواب یه مشت تحصیل کرده که تو دهه شصت گیر کردندبه لجن کشیدی و تو این استان اگر نخوای امپراطوری جنابعالی تو ادارات جوان های تحصیلکرده را راه نمیده و اگر بخوای با دیپلم آنها را به درجه انسانیت میرسانی و با مدرک دکترا مدیر و ریس و پیمانکار رانت خوار میکنی چون پستش به شما و شما پشتت به نابغه اقتصادی #نوبخت در استان #گیلان خوش هست مثل صلاحیت گرفتنت در دور پیش .
شماها اگر امثال آین جوان ها اگر سیاسی نباشند سیاسی میکنیدشان 
دوستان #دلواپس و فدایان #عربية در یک جمله یک جواب منطقی بابت آین التماس این جوان بدهید عقل میگه وقتی من با یکی نمیتونم سرشاخ بشم یا طرفش نمیرم یا اگر قراره هر روز ببینمش یک جور باهاش کنار میام غیر این خودم ضربه می خورم . ای کاش جنگ با توپ و تفنگ میکردیم تا تکلبفمون مشخص بود حد اقل ارزش پاسپورتمون بالاتر از پاسپورت افغان عراق میشد بیچاره کردین نسل #دهه_شصت را بیچاره کردین جواب هرمهدرا بدید جواب مارا نمیتونست بدید

text:
#twft52 i wrote a long caption for this but maybe it was too long to upload properly because it keeps telling me something went wrong.
. 
this past week’s prompt was “forget”. .

i’ll just share the following excerpt from kahlil gibran’s “on joy & sorrow” from the prophet because it really taught me to accept all of me: the good, the bad, and the ugly. i wouldn’t be who i am today without all of it. while i still have much to work on, i appreciate the person i have become today.
.
“your joy is your sorrow unmasked.
and the selfsame well from which your laughter rises was oftentimes filled with your tears.
and how else can it be?
the deeper that sorrow carves into your being, the more joy you can contain.
is not the cup that holds your wine the very cup that was burned in the potter's oven?
and is not the lute that soothes your spirit, the very wood that was hollowed with knives?
when you are joyous, look deep into your heart and you shall find it is only that which has given you sorrow that is giving you joy.
when you are sorrowful look again in your heart, and you shall see that in truth you are weeping for that which has been your delight.”
.
you are not alone and you don’t have to be ever again. whether you feel vulnerable, scared, lost, fearful, angry, hatred, self-hatred, helpless, hopeless, etc. know that there is someone out there who understands and/or empathizes. i am on this journey with the rest of the beautiful #survivors out there and each day, i say #metoo . #ibelieveher and #ibelieveinyou .
#metoomovement #intj #intjfemale #ibelievesurvivors #change #onedayatatime #mentalhealthawareness #anxiety #depression #nyc #timesup #bekind #strength #courage #believe
name: evolvewiththeflow

text:
they mentioned him again on quotidien! the guest was augustin trapenard, who interviewed him last year for his radio show boomerang (it's on youtube for those who haven't heard it yet)
they were discussing ''sore points'', cause yann (the host) thinks he seems to avoid these subjects (he recently interviewed bruce weber but didn't ask him about the sexual harassment he's accused of)
basically, in this video, yann asks if he sometimes makes deals with his guests not to talk about a specific sore subject. augustin says ''never'', like that time when he asked timothée chalamet straight in the eyes about #metoo while he'd been asked not to, and the interview almost ended there because he was furious (i don't remember that, i'll need to listen to it again!) but eventually answered the question.
.
.
.
that's it, no big news, no scoop, nothing that will end the drought but i wanted to share that with you because he's still not as famous as he should be here in france so i'm always happy to hear his name on tv, especially at peak viewing time 😊
.
.
.
.
.

text:
singer r. kelly faces new sex abuse charges in #metoo era
#
new york (reuters) - more than a decade ago, the singer r. kelly was acquitted of child pornography charges after a trial in which the alleged underage victim did not testify against him. singer robert kelly, known as r. kelly, appears in a booking photo provided by the chicago police department in chicago, illinois, u.s., on february 23, 2019. courtesy chicago police department/handout via reuters now the embattled grammy-winning performer faces new sexual abuse allegations in an era when – thanks in large part to the #metoo movement – victims are more willing to come forward, and their stories more likely to be accepted by both law enforcement and, eventually, a jury. prosecutors said the current case was brought on behalf of four victims, including three who were between the ages of 13 and 17 when kelly allegedly abused them. “one obvious difference is that there are now women who have come forward and who are willing to cooperate with the prosecution,” said deborah tuerkheimer, a professor at northwestern university who studies sexual assault cases. “in some ways, it really is a microcosm of what is happening in our culture. we’re moving toward this greater receptivity to accusations of sexual…

text:
#sabrinaimpacciatore a #farecritica: "la parola chiave del nostro paese è discriminazione". tra gli ospiti del festival anche il regista #danieleluchetti.
lamezia terme, 23 febbraio 2019 - "invidio gli attori maschi, che possono interpretare ruoli anche molto complessi, violenti, cosa molto poco diffusa per noi donne", ha esordito così ieri sera #sabrinaimpacciatore, ospite della quarta e penultima serata di #farecritica, il festival dedicato alla critica cinematografica e teatrale diretto da #gianlorenzofranzì (lamezia terme, 19-24 febbraio 2019).
l'attrice ha proseguito il discorso iniziato da #cristianapaternò sull'impoverimento culturale del nostro paese che è anche la causa della crisi della critica cinematografica. d'altronde, il maschilismo imperante della nostra società non è altro che la dimostrazione di una decadenza culturale, "una società che concepisce le donne come oggetti di arredamento con una scadenza, è una società impoverita".
"il nostro è un paese la cui parola chiave è discriminazione. viviamo in una cultura endemicamente maschilista, dove tutto va molto più a rilento", ha continuato l'attrice, riportando anche l'esempio del movimento americano #metoo. "a los angeles - infatti - è avvenuta una vera e propria rivoluzione culturale. in italia, invece, non è cambiato niente".
il "grave impoverimento culturale dell'italia, che è stata a lungo un faro nel mondo, porta ad una decadenza che investe ogni ambito della sfera artistico-culturale, che va dalla recitazione alla critica. l'assenza di preparazione nel nostro paese non è considerata un disvalore perché non c’è meritocrazia in questa società".
un degrado, questo, che investe soprattutto le giovani generazioni, come ha riportato lo stesso #danieleluchetti (anche lui ospite della manifestazione) che ogni giorno riscontra queste difficoltà con i suoi studenti del #centrosperimentale di cinematografia di roma...
[link nelle storie]

text:
necesito el feminismo porque...
porque hoy que me iba a vestir pensé "no, ese vestido no porque no voy a ver a ningún hombre.... al carajo, no necesito arreglarme para nadie más que para mí."
porque me da miedo salir a la calle y no regresar más a casa.
porque a una de mís amigas no la dejan salir si no es con uno de sus hermanos.
porque me violaron dos veces, tuve otro intento de violación y los 3 casos quedaron impunes.
porque en méxico mueren 9 mujeres al día por el machismo.
porque ya no quiero ser vista como objeto de consumo.
porque no me puedo vestir como quiero sin "provocar" a los hombres.
porque ser mujer todavía se utiliza como insulto.
porque las otras no son mi competencia...
.
por esto y muchas más razones es que necesito el feminismo... y tu?
.
.
.
.
.
#feminismoparatodxs #sevaacaer #feminismo #mujeres #vergavioladoraalalicuadora #unidassomosmasfuertes #mexicosinjusticia #equidad #estoyharta #strongwomen #notacompetition #metoo #noesno #niunamas #machismo #mexicofeminista #patriarcado

text:
🎧 in the wake of the #metoo movement, artists and professors of the csun campus join the conversation on whether it’s possible to separate an artist’s work from their controversial biographies.
—
during the past few years, sexual abuse allegations against many artists and entertainers have been exposed by news outlets and social media.
—
despite all the allegations and consequences, artists who have been accused of sexual violence are continuing to make art flourish. the question then arises: is it possible to separate the art from the artist?
—
🗞 read more about this story on our website!
—
📝: sean hanafi
📸: sarah hofstedt

(i had the pleasure of spontaneously participating in panel discussion with notable women including forbes india - feb 18, 2019)

text: in conclusion. this was not the first attempt, many trials and errors, many irrelevant unproductive dangerous moments, lots of studying, for the dream of time travel. although looking back, for healing purposes and evolution, there was a phase in getting here that may have helped. not certain to recommend it, at least not initially; yet it was an important part of the journey. to remain aware of self, internal and external, balancing right and left brain. this is when the string ball theory was assembled. challenge understanding, approach hyper critical; to levels much like we've all been experiencing externally, in an internal sense. the ambidextrous phase, not perfected, and not continued beyond those couple of months, alternating focus or trying too. to fully sync out of traumas. i didn't know electromagnetics and dna, were together back then, just light studies mostly, electromagnetics; that's the only biological study i worked on in private in front of others for the project. kinda sensitive to light, is apparent. it does not teach you to read or judge others, or yourself, not self conscious in an inhibiting way, just aware from inside out, can't control others just attempting to sense danger, it was a weird phase. for greater understanding and yeah staying in sync with myself and out of badger hands. also like learning, and reading described in a previous post, introducing new information, perspectives expands our knowledge, in any topic or life experience, it can be frustrating and hurts the brain a bit, but the previous information is being expanded on. not in a way of letting yourself die, taking an understood thought, brought into a more vast understanding. i am done with posting regularly, maybe occasional random updates. staying active in the movement, of coarse. aswell more life experiences to grow from progress and maintenance will be continued in more private personal formats. thanks to all those who've been supportive, and positive influences, those who've gone before us, protected and expanded our freedoms, lifelong friends, maybe i'll see you in the future, or meet you there. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors

text: while narcissistic abuse is a very serious form of domestic violence, the cycle of abuse is slightly different.  first, it starts with a narcissistic injury, whether real or perceived.  the narcissist has been insulted or endured an injury to his ego.  second, he will project those feelings of inferiority onto you, known as a narcissistic rage.  they can not process and accept derogatory feelings that go against their fake facade or false self.  third, they blame you or others for their rage, it’s not ever their responsibility.  if you had not done xyz, then they would not have gotten angry.  fourth, the rage and victim hood elevates the narcissist injury, making them feel empowered again, special and superior.  and round and round it goes.  it’s a continual cycle.  #narcissisticabuse #narcabuserecovery #narcissistsurvivor #survivor #parentalalienation #targetedindividuals #domesticviolence #childabuse

text: this is the song that i wrote back in 2014 ... before i was sexually harassed and stalked and lost my mind 💜 and had to step up as kamala into mama kamala. . . (call me ronnie rom com..) this song, space gimme space, at that time circles was inspired by thinking, longing, hopes and dreams and love, and was big time inspired by prince, as it was written when the artist first visited me in spirit, 👻 before he passed on. feel so close by calvin harris was another big inspiration of this song. jessica searcy became mama kamala and it is exactly the way that it had to be. 💫a song of space. being a space cadet myself in sickness and in health. ✌🏼 also, of kindly saying "fuck off," 🎆🙌🏻🌌 to sex- obsessed, cowardly, boundary-violating creepo's. as a big dreamer and manifester of realities, often i've whether it is harsh, cross or cray-cray, did what i had to do to keep my very important "green time" (alone time, space) with no explanations, excuses, just action; no justifications, or apologies. so dèsole ☀️ if i've offended. sometimes it's to our advantage for people to think that we are crazy. ✌🏼 space gimme space. like to these black magick freaks- you're dull and weak. freedom is a value as much as independence. so don't talk to me, let's meditate and telepathy on it so in my energy i've embraced... 💜💜 ✨ out tomorrow on itunes and spotify and more- watch for it. i'll be posting the link on the account for the artist, mama kamala (@mamakamala) when i find it myself! 🎆🔮💜 this song is totally dedicated to those who hear themselves in it but most especially to the essence of the feminine energy of ida, or of yin, and of the ☯️ egyptian goddess, nepthys, who says: "there is no doing. it's already done." 🙏🏼 she was there for isis, me in my darkness, with anubis, too,  to help me shine a bright light for none but me, i & myself. always shining my light on others, it's time to take it all back. what is borrowed was just that. 🙏🏼🌌✨ a perfect song to be starting pisces season with. . . #dreamer #doer #be #beliver #lml #spacegimmespace #pisces #noregrets #metoo #dream #mamakamala #sansregrets #sundayfunday #hope 💕🌙🌌🎆🌌🎆🔮💜💕 #mamakamalamusic #consentishawt #detour

🎆🔮💜 this song is totally dedicated to those who hear themselves in it but most especially to the essence of the feminine energy of ida, or of yin, and of the ☯️ egyptian goddess, nepthys, who says: "there is no doing. it is already done." 🙏🏼 she was there for isis, me in my darkness, with anubis, too,  to help me shine a bright light for none but me, i & myself. always shining my light on others, it is time to take it all back. what is borrowed was just that. 🙏🏼🌌✨ a perfect song to be starting pisces season with. . . #dreamer #doer #be #beliver #lml #spacegimmespace #pisces #noregrets #metoo #dream #mamakamala #sansregrets #sundayfunday #hope 💕🌙🌌🎆🌌🎆🔮💜💕 #mamakamalamusic #consentishawt #detour

text:
♡2019年2月24日②♡
娘のスマホを操作したら周りの社員が反応した件。社内の人間が私のスマホを遠隔で覗き見る事に関しては犯罪であるが
会社を守りたいという事からそうなったのだろう。
でもそもそもなぜ娘のスマホまで監視していたのか？
中1の時に公園で遊んでいて警察に補導された。
でも後で聞いたら22:00過ぎてなかったのにと本人は言う。
おそらく通報だろうとは思うが誰からか？
その日は確か問題のセクハラ上司の森岡が異動になった#塚口 工場の前#つかしん の#ワールドビュッフェ に行ってたはず。
娘がlineでやり取りしてるのを見ていてわざと待ち時間を増やし時間を遅くさせた可能性もある。
たかこの言う#ネグレクト の証拠を作るために

その他、本人が雑なのかスマホは3回壊れ、カバンのジッパーは必ず潰す
買って3日で割れた水筒も最初は気づいたら割れていたと言っていたが最近になりあれは落としたと言いだした。
2回目買いなおしてから私も何回か落としてるが割れません。
そしてもう一つ引っかかるのが買ったお店を私が気に入っていたのに閉店した事。
#梅田 なのでヤンマーの庭。
そんな事簡単に出来るだろう。
言いがかりだと言い返されるかもしれないが
私が気に入っていたお店が閉店したのは一件だけじゃない。
10件くらいになるから言い返すよ「偶然とは思えません」って…
・
・

text:
and i’m back! this past week has been crazy. i’ve seen lawyers, new therapists and trying to sought out paperwork 😩 on friday i worked for 10 hours and i was on my feet all day which left me physically and emotionally drained but i had a party that night😓 i had another fight at the party with my boyfriend because he was falling behind my back and controlling me and i was really hurt but when i talk about it he never listens 🙃 i went home with my childhood best friend and our mums hung out all day and it was so nostalgic and i felt happy and safe for the first time in awhile💗 today i plan to go to the movies with mum and hopefully eat lunch and snacks without having anxiety, i’m trying so hard to have a good day 😅 i hope everyone is doing well 💗💗💗 (this sausage roll was from the cutest bakery in my friend’s home town that i’ve never been to before but it was amazing 😍) -addy✨

text:
today was payday for me. as i settle into my new #inittowinit life, i decided to stay in this evening and open a bottle of #wine and hang out with my monthly planner. had a couple of set backs this month with an emergency room pet visit, valentines day and a bit of feeling sorry for myself. a few things i am learning and loving amongst you amazing people. you guys really are a blessing. i have some pretty big relationship stuff going on and several of you have just been a god send today. support means so much even from strangers because the human spirit is alive and thriving and we are made for joy. and another thing is we are all just trying to make it from one day to the next in a world that screams instant gratification is yours for the taking. we are taking control back. i am blessed to follow so many of you who pour out your wisdom each day. you guys bring me joy. thank you! #❤️
.
.
.
.

text:
"it has to be fake."
"fox news is saying not."
"fox news would say whatever makes the most people tune in to fox news." ~ naomi alderman, the power
⚡️
i really stepped out of my comfort zone this month and read two dystopian novels i've heard so much about - one disturbing and one a real page turner.
⚡️
never let me go is worlds away from the remains of the day.  narrated by kathy who is trying to come to terms with her childhood and the fate that awaits her and her friends.  the students at hailsham "school" are in fact clones bred as future organ donors.  reading this book, i had a sense of déjà vu and realised that it was the story of a film i'd only partially seen starring keira knightley, carey mulligan, andrew garfield and charlotte rampling.  it was creepy so i turned it off as i didn't want to watch it.  however, i persevered with the book and felt so sad at the end.  i still think i'll give the film a miss though.
⚡️
on the other hand, i couldn't put the power down.  all over the world girls are discovering a special power and soon men find they've lost control.  with power comes evil.  the day of the girls has come, but where will it end? a fascinating look at female empowerment in the days of #metoo #girlpower . thanks anna 😘@dempstersbookshelf for such a great book.
⚡️
do you read outside your preferred genre(s)? have you liked books more than you expected?
⚡️

never let me go is worlds away from the remains of the day.  narrated by kathy who is trying to come to terms with her childhood and the fate that awaits her and her friends.  the students at hailsham "school" are in fact clones bred as future organ donors.  reading this book, i had a sense of déjà vu and realised that it was the story of a film i'd only paially seen starring keira knightley, carey mulligan, andrew garfield and charlotte rampling.  it was creepy so i turned it off as i didn't want to watch it.  however, i persevered with the book and felt so sad at the end.  i still think i'll give the film a miss though.
⚡️
on the other hand, i couldn't put the power down.  all over the world girls are discovering a special power and soon men find they've lost control.  with power comes evil.  the day of the girls has come, but where will it end? a fascinating look at female empowerment in the days of   . thanks anna 😘 for such a great book.
⚡️
do you read outside your preferred genre(s)? have you liked books more than you expected?
⚡️

text:
12 - h e r  s t o r y

a graphic essay on the #metoo movement in india. 
this essay addresses sexual harassment at the workplace in india, and how many have reacted to it. 
it is a deeper look at the #metoo movement in india, for which i’ve collaborated with the polis project ( @thepolisproject ). if you think this message is important, relevant or have faced similar questions in discussions about the movement, please consider sharing this! 
the entire essay is available on the polis project’s website, and is linked in my bio. it’s best viewed on a larger screen, so pleaseee do me and your eyesight a favour and check it out on the website!
